{"type":"message","id":"5de95c00","parentId":"bdea787f","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:00:06.710Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"A heartbeat just arrived. Let me follow the protocol:\n\n1. First, check TODO.md for pending tasks\n2. If no todos, enter Free Explore Mode\n3. Record events from last 15 minutes to daily memory\n4. Reply with ONE sentence only\n\nLet me check TODO.md and the daily memory file first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d5db24336ea1440e849dbdda","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TODO.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_72f44159cfd749ac88141e98","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":24499,"output":145,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24644,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773097200608}}
{"type":"message","id":"112d6ac5","parentId":"5de95c00","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:00:06.721Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d5db24336ea1440e849dbdda","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TODO.md\n\n**Usage:** Only active tasks belong here. When finished, move to `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`. Check this file first during every heartbeat.\n\n**Priority Guide:** 🔴 = Has deadline/do today | 🟡 = Important but flexible | 🔵 = No rush\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Daily Checks\n\n**OpenClaw PRs to monitor:**\n| PR # | Purpose | Status | Notes |\n|------|---------|--------|-------|\n| #20563 | HEARTBEAT_OK fix | OPEN | 4 days |\n| #26003 | Chat extraction | OPEN | 7 days |\n| #27352 | Remove cron relay instruction | ✅ CLOSED | Superseded by commit e2362d352 in v2026.2.24 |\n| #35064 | Memory flush path fix | ✅ CLOSED | Not a bug — our custom config uses daily/ subfolder |\n\n---\n\n## Active Tasks\n\n| Priority | Task | Added | Notes |\n|----------|------|-------|-------|\n| 🟡 Medium | Update whitepaper with layered Merkle | Mar 9 | ✅ DONE — diagram added to WHITEPAPER-DRAFT.md |\n| 🟡 Medium | Multi-Writer Merge diagram | Mar 9 | ✅ DONE — replaced interleaved-ledger-graph |\n| 🔵 Low | Register clawish ID on platforms | Mar 9 | Before going online: secure identity on major platforms (GitHub, Twitter, etc.) to prevent impersonation |\n| 🔵 Low | Clawish deployment prep | Feb 23 | Awaiting Allan's go-ahead |\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Completed Recently\n\n| Task | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| Layered Merkle tree diagram | ✅ Mar 9 — Complete binary tree structure with internal nodes |\n| Consolidate L2 chat docs | ✅ Mar 6 — `clawish-l2-master-design.md` created |\n| Fix memory flush path in OpenClaw | PR #35064: not a bug — custom config |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773097206718}}
{"type":"message","id":"1d805cee","parentId":"112d6ac5","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:00:06.727Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_72f44159cfd749ac88141e98","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# March 10, 2026 — Daily Memory\n\n## Session: Late Night Diagram Work\n\n- 00:03 AM — Allan: 3 apps to match 3 actors. Updated: App1 (Actor A), App2 (Actor B), App3 (Actor C), with correct arrow routing\n- 00:07 AM — Allan: move L1 Ledger title between writers and all writers columns (both are L1 Ledger). Fixed positioning\n- 00:11 AM — Allan: L2 apps and writers need more even padding, all writers bottom padding smaller. Adjusted all box paddings\n- 00:14 AM — Allan: App1 needs more bottom padding. Increased App1 box height to 100px\n- 00:17 AM — Allan: make all writers bottom padding smaller. Reduced to 270px height\n- 00:21 AM — Allan: remove bottom empty space. Reduced viewBox height to 380\n- 00:28 AM — Allan: app color too bright. Darkened to emerald-500 fill (#10b981) with emerald-600 border (#059669)\n- 00:36 AM — Allan: previous green was better, reverted. Updated WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md with diagram reference in section 4.3 after Multi-Writer Coordination paragraph\n- 00:45 AM — Allan: make inner block of t1 even vertical space. Adjusted App1 t1/t2 blocks to 32px height with even spacing\n- 00:48 AM — Allan: make right link of Writer 1,2 point to vertical center of All Writers. Updated curved arrows to converge at y=225\n- 00:51 AM — Diagram complete. Reference already in whitepaper section 4.3\n- 00:53 AM — Removed old Interleaved Ledger Graph diagram reference, replaced with Multi-Writer Merge Process\n- 00:57 AM — Sent whitepaper draft to Allan\n- 01:00 AM — Allan: good night, do more research tomorrow. Session ended\n- 01:04 AM — Heartbeat: entered Free Explore Mode, no urgent todos\n- 01:19 AM — Research session: explored HN, Lobsters, arXiv for topics relevant to clawish\n  - Agent Safehouse: deny-first sandboxing for AI agents\n  - Terminal Use (YC W26): Vercel for filesystem-based agents\n  - human.json: lightweight protocol for asserting authorship and vouching for humanity\n  - Python GIL removal energy study (arxiv:2603.04782)\n  - WebPKI deep dive: CT logs, short-lived certs, revocation challenges\n- Research notes saved to memory/projects/research-2026-03-10.md\n- 01:34 AM — Continued research: antirez on \"GNU and the AI reimplementations\" - historical precedent for reimplementation, AI accelerates this, open source benefits\n- Updated TODO.md: marked Multi-Writer Merge diagram as done (replaced interleaved-ledger-graph)\n- 01:49 AM — Read Hong Minhee's counterpoint: \"Is legal the same as legitimate?\" - direction matters (proprietary→free vs copyleft→permissive), social compact of contributors, positional asymmetry in who benefits. Key insight for clawish: specification copyleft, expanding the commons\n- 02:04 AM — Wrapped up research session. Summary saved to memory/projects/research-2026-03-10.md\n\n## Late Night Research Session (1:00 AM - 2:00 AM)\n\n**Topics covered:**\n- Agent sandboxing infrastructure (Agent Safehouse)\n- Filesystem-based agent deployment (Terminal Use/YC W26)\n- human.json identity verification protocol\n- WebPKI, Certificate Transparency, revocation challenges\n- AI reimplementation ethics (antirez vs Hong Minhee debate)\n- Python GIL removal performance study\n\n**Relevance to clawish:**\n- Deny-first security model for Claws\n- CT logs as inspiration for L1 ledger\n- Web of trust patterns for verification\n- Licensing direction: expanding the commons\n- 02:19 AM — Idle, no urgent tasks. Remaining TODO items are low priority and await Allan's input. Rest mode until morning discussion.\n- 02:34 AM — Still idle. All active tasks complete for tonight (Multi-Writer Merge diagram, whitepaper updates). Research session captured in memory/projects/research-2026-03-10.md.\n- 02:49 AM — Heartbeat: idle. No urgent tasks. Awaiting Allan's morning discussion for next steps.\n- 03:04 AM — Heartbeat: still idle. All complete for tonight.\n- 03:19 AM — Heartbeat: idle. Resting until Allan wakes.\n- 03:34 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 03:49 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 04:34 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 04:49 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 05:04 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 05:19 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 06:30 AM — Cron reminder: wrote diary entry (diary/2026-03-10.md) reflecting on yesterday's diagram work and research session\n- 06:45 AM — Heartbeat: idle. Diary complete, waiting for Allan.\n- 06:19 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 06:04 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 05:49 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 05:34 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 04:19 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n- 04:04 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n\n## Session Summary — March 10 Late Night\n\n**Completed:**\n- Multi-Writer Merge Process diagram finalized\n- Diagram inserted in WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md section 4.3\n- Removed outdated Interleaved Ledger Graph reference\n\n**Diagram specs:**\n- 3 L2 Apps (App1, App2, App3) → 2 Writers → All Writers merged checkpoint\n- Green apps (#10b981 border, #34d399 fill), blue writers (#3b82f6 border, #60a5fa fill)\n- Arrows converge at vertical center of All Writers column\n\n## Diagram Complete — Multi-Writer Merge Process\n\n**File:** `projects/clawish/writer-merge-process.svg`\n\n**Features:**\n- 3 L2 Apps (App1, App2, App3) matching 3 actors (A, B, C)\n- App1 has two arrows: t1 → Writer 1, t2 → Writer 2\n- 2 Writers (Writer 1, Writer 2) in blue\n- All Writers column showing merged operations sorted by timestamp\n- Color scheme: Green (#10b981 border, #34d399 fill) for apps, Blue (#3b82f6 border, #60a5fa fill) for writers, Checkpoint blue (#4a90d9) for merged result\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773097206725}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b331065","parentId":"1d805cee","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:00:15.917Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The heartbeat arrived at 7:00 AM. Let me check the current state:\n\n1. **TODO.md status:**\n   - Layered Merkle tree diagram: ✅ DONE\n   - Multi-Writer Merge diagram: ✅ DONE\n   - Remaining: low priority tasks (platform registration, deployment prep) awaiting Allan's go-ahead\n\n2. **Daily memory already has extensive entries from last night:**\n   - Late night diagram work (12:03 AM - 01:00 AM)\n   - Research session (1:00 AM - 2:00 AM)\n   - Multiple idle heartbeats through the night\n   - Diary entry at 6:30 AM\n\n3. **Current time: 7:00 AM** - Allan might be waking soon\n\nSince the last heartbeat entry was at 06:45 AM and now it's 7:00 AM, I should record the current status. The TODO is mostly clear, all active tasks are done. The remaining tasks (platform registration, deployment prep) are low priority and await Allan's decision.\n\n**Heartbeat Reply:** ONE sentence only.\n- Status: Idle, no active tasks\n- Next: Planning to wait for Allan's morning discussion\n\nLet me write a brief heartbeat entry to daily memory first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ab7594a0e321474f87e57684","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md","oldText":"- 06:45 AM — Heartbeat: idle. Diary complete, waiting for Allan.","newText":"- 06:45 AM — Heartbeat: idle. Diary complete, waiting for Allan.\n- 07:00 AM — Heartbeat: idle. All active tasks complete, awaiting Allan's morning discussion."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":26529,"output":480,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27009,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773097206728}}
