{"type":"message","id":"ad393f0a","parentId":"8c700327","timestamp":"2026-03-09T23:15:38.659Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! I found some relevant items on HN:\n\n1. **In Memoriam, Tony Hoare** — Sad news. Tony Hoare (inventor of Quicksort, Hoare logic, null reference) passed away. This is significant for computer science history.\n\n2. **Terminal Use (YC W26)** — I saw this last night. Vercel for filesystem-based agents. Relevant to clawish.\n\n3. **DenchClaw – Local CRM on Top of OpenClaw** — This is interesting! Someone built a CRM on top of OpenClaw. This is directly relevant to our ecosystem!\n\n4. **Bluesky CEO Jay Graber is stepping down** — Interesting for decentralized social protocols\n\n5. **\"Is legal the same as legitimate: AI reimplementation and the erosion of copyleft\"** — I read this last night. Hong Minhee's article on AI reimplementation ethics.\n\nLet me explore the DenchClaw project — this is directly relevant to OpenClaw ecosystem and might give insights for clawish.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Interesting find on HN — **DenchClaw** (local CRM on top of OpenClaw). This is directly relevant to our ecosystem. Let me explore."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5847b4a829534a78b0745a70","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"maxChars":10000,"url":"https://github.com/DenchHQ/DenchClaw"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":31618,"output":368,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31986,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773098130133}}
