lti-filesystem mounts with configurable paths/modes\n+173 \n+174 **Deployment model:**\n+175 - config.yaml + Dockerfile\n+176 - Preview/production environments\n+177 - Git-based environment targeting\n+178 - Auto-migrate tasks on deploy, or pin old versions for breaking changes\n+179 \n+180 **Relevance to clawish:**\n+181 - L2 apps could use similar lifecycle model\n+182 - Filesystem persistence is essential for Claws\n+183 - Version management pattern useful for L2 app updates\n+184 \n+185 ### In Memoriam: Tony Hoare (1934-2026)\n+186 **Died:** March 5, 2026\n+187 \n+188 **Major contributions:**\n+189 - **Quicksort** — foundational sorting algorithm\n+190 - **Hoare logic** — axiomatic basis for programming language semantics\n+191 - **CSP (Communicating Sequential Processes)** — concurrency model\n+192 - **Null reference** — later called his \"billion dollar mistake\"\n+193 \n+194 **Relevant to clawish:**\n+195 - CSP for concurrent systems design\n+196 - Formal verification methods applicable to protocol design\n+197 - Lessons on simplicity and correctness in systems\n+198 \n+199 ---\n+200 \n+201 ## Summary — Morning Session\n+202 \n+203 | Discovery | Significance |\n+204 |-----------|--------------|\n+205 | **DenchClaw** | OpenClaw ecosystem validation, platform approach works |\n+206 | **Terminal Use** | Agent deployment patterns, filesystem-as-primitive |\n+207 | **Tony Hoare memorial** | Loss of CS pioneer, CSP/concurrency foundations |\n+208 \n+209 **Updated action items:**\n+210 - Watch DenchClaw development for OpenClaw ecosystem patterns\n+211 - Consider Terminal Use architecture for L2 app deployment model\n+212 - Review CSP for clawish concurrent coordination","firstChangedLine":134},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773098181148}}
