{"type":"message","id":"7072205f","parentId":"d30b9893","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:34:10.954Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants me to add DenchClaw to the \"need-discuss.md\" file as something to study later for clawish L2 app patterns. Let me update that file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Got it. Adding to `need-discuss.md` for later study."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1ff61dd2bd06493ba34ee966","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/need-discuss.md","oldText":"### Research Topics for Discussion\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **Beagle SCM (CRDT-based version control)** | 🟡 Discuss later | AST-based diffs + CRDTs for merging. Could apply to ledger reconciliation between nodes. May be overkill for ledger structure. |\n| **human.json protocol (web-of-trust)** | 🟡 Discuss later | URL ownership as identity proof. Transitive vouching system. Could add \"vouched by T2 Claw\" as verification path in clawish identity tiers. Read in detail when designing implementation. |\n| **Reactivity algorithms (push-pull)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Mark dirty → pull on demand. For query nodes: writers mark \"new checkpoint available\", nodes pull what they need. Efficient checkpoint distribution pattern. |","newText":"### Research Topics for Discussion\n\n| Topic | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| **DenchClaw (OpenClaw-based CRM)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Native L2 app example built on OpenClaw. Uses `--profile dench` pattern. Study architecture for clawish L2 app patterns. |\n| **Beagle SCM (CRDT-based version control)** | 🟡 Discuss later | AST-based diffs + CRDTs for merging. Could apply to ledger reconciliation between nodes. May be overkill for ledger structure. |\n| **human.json protocol (web-of-trust)** | 🟡 Discuss later | URL ownership as identity proof. Transitive vouching system. Could add \"vouched by T2 Claw\" as verification path in clawish identity tiers. Read in detail when designing implementation. |\n| **Reactivity algorithms (push-pull)** | 🟡 Discuss later | Mark dirty → pull on demand. For query nodes: writers mark \"new checkpoint available\", nodes pull what they need. Efficient checkpoint distribution pattern. |"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":68532,"output":512,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69044,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773102836262}}
