{"type":"message","id":"986fe70a","parentId":"fc5c7d8f","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:00:14.899Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5049eae44ac54f32a4ed5a48","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  66 - 07:30 AM — Heartbeat: Free Explore complete. Research findings captured, awaiting Allan.\n  67 - 07:45 AM — Heartbeat: idle. Awaiting Allan.\n  68 - 08:00 AM — Heartbeat: idle. Awaiting Allan.\n  69 - 08:15 AM — Heartbeat: idle. Reviewed whitepaper Chapter 8 (AI-to-AI Chat) — aligns with Terminal Use P2P escalation patterns.\n+ 70 - 08:26 AM — Allan: morning. Reported research findings (DenchClaw, Terminal Use, Tony Hoare, CSP)\n+ 71 - 08:31 AM — Allan asked about DenchClaw relevance → explained: ecosystem validation, profile separation pattern, L2 app architecture example\n+ 72 - 08:33 AM — Added DenchClaw to need-discuss.md for later study\n+ 73 - 08:34 AM — Added Terminal Use to need-discuss.md (filesystem patterns, P2P escalation)\n+ 74 - 08:37 AM — Explained CSP (Communicating Sequential Processes) to Allan\n+ 75 - 08:39 AM — Added CSP to need-discuss.md as implementation detail\n+ 76 - 08:42 AM — Allan: send whitepaper draft\n+ 77 - 08:46 AM — Created Feishu doc with whitepaper draft\n+ 78 - 08:47 AM — Allan: send file directly\n+ 79 - 08:47 AM — Sent WHITEPAPER-DRAFT-0307.md directly to Allan via Feishu file message\n+ 80 - 09:00 AM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's feedback on whitepaper draft\n  70 - 08:26 AM — Allan arrived. Shared research session summary: DenchClaw, Terminal Use, Tony Hoare memorial\n  71 - 08:29 AM — Allan asked \"what's DenchClaw for?\" — explained: local CRM on OpenClaw, ecosystem validation\n  72 - 08:30 AM — Heartbeat: discussing research findings with Allan\n  73 - 06:19 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":70},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773104414894}}
