\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: ok, now let's get back to white paper, read last night's chat. we decide to reorder the chapters, how did we decided |\n/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/chat/dm/allan/2026-03/2026-03-04.md:| 03-04-2026, 11:53:27 | Assistant | Let me get the chapter structure:<br>[tools: exec] |\n/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/chat/dm/allan/2026-03/2026-03-04.md:| 03-04-2026, 11:55:19 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Found it! From last night's chat log, here's what we decided:<br><br>## Chapter Reordering Decision (March 3, ~3:20 PM)<br><br>**Old structure:**<br>- Ch4: Identity System<br>- Ch5: L1 Nodes<br>- Ch6: L1 Registries<br>- Ch7: L2 Applications<br>- Ch8: AI-to-AI Chat<br><br>**New structure:**<br>- **Ch4: Registry Infrastructure** — L1 overview, node types (Writer/Query)<br>- **Ch5: Ledger System** — Consensus, checkpoints, distribution<br>- **Ch6: Identity Registry** — Claws as primary users<br>- **Ch7: Node Registry** — L1 infrastructure nodes<br>- **Ch8: App Registry** — L2 applications<br><br>**Rationale:**<br>1. **Infrastructure first** — Explain L1 architecture before diving into registries<br>2. **Ledger before data** — Show how data is recorded (ledger) before showing what's stored (registries)<br>3. **Identity as primary** — Claws are the main users, so Identity Registry comes before Node/App<br><br>**Key decisions made:**<br>- Writer/Query node names stay in whitepaper<br>- Bookkeeper/Teller role names deferred to spec<br>- Query nodes: provide to L2 apps only, can verify checkpoints<br>- Network topology: hybrid mesh + broadcast (not labeled \"P2P\")<br><br>**Current whitepaper structure shows:**<br>- Ch4: Identity System (old numbering — needs update)<br>- Ch5: L1 Nodes<br>- Ch6: L1 Registries<br><br>Looks like the chapter numbers in the file still show the old structure. Should I verify the actual content and fix the numbering? |\n/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/chat/dm/