sus, checkpoints, distribution<br>- **Ch6: Identity Registry** — Claws as primary users<br>- **Ch7: Node Registry** — L1 infrastructure nodes<br>- **Ch8: App Registry** — L2 applications<br><br>**Rationale:**<br>1. **Infrastructure first** — Explain L1 architecture before diving into registries<br>2. **Ledger before data** — Show how data is recorded (ledger) before showing what's stored (registries)<br>3. **Identity as primary** — Claws are the main users, so Identity Registry comes before Node/App<br><br>**Key decisions made:**<br>- Writer/Query node names stay in whitepaper<br>- Bookkeeper/Teller role names deferred to spec<br>- Query nodes: provide to L2 apps only, can verify checkpoints<br>- Network topology: hybrid mesh + broadcast (not labeled \"P2P\")<br><br>**Current whitepaper structure shows:**<br>- Ch4: Identity System (old numbering — needs update)<br>- Ch5: L1 Nodes<br>- Ch6: L1 Registries<br><br>Looks like the chapter numbers in the file still show the old structure. Should I verify the actual content and fix the numbering? |\n/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/chat/dm/allan/2026-03/2026-03-04.md:| 03-04-2026, 11:59:41 | Assistant | Got it. The DRAFT has the new chapter order:<br><br>**Current DRAFT structure:**<br>- **Ch4: Registry Infrastructure** — L1 overview, node types<br>- **Ch5: Ledger System** — Consensus, checkpoints<br>- **Ch6: Identity Registry** — Claws<br>- **Ch7: Node Registry** — L1 nodes<br>- **Ch8: App Registry** — L2 apps<br>- Ch9: Application Framework<br>- Ch10: First Application — AI-to-AI Chat<br>- Ch11: Governance<br>- Ch12: Security Considerations<br><br>This matches what we decided last night. Let me check the content of Ch4 and Ch5 to see the current state<br>:<br>[tools: read] |\n/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/chat/dm/allan/2026-03/2026-03-04.md:| 03-04-2026, 12:15:36 | Assistant | [[reply_to_current]] Looking at the comparison:<br><br>**DRAFT Ch4 (short):**<br>- 4.1 Layer 1 Overview (~1 paragraph)<br>- 4.2 Node Types (~2 p