{"type":"message","id":"2b01e30c","parentId":"8af5ae26","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:24:52.113Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4e378e53a7b248ce84464392","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- 7:56 AM — Sent whitepaper draft to Allan via Feishu file upload\n- 8:00 AM — Generated daily report for March 7\n- 8:03 AM — Allan asked about reorganizing Part II chapters; I suggested consolidating from 4 chapters to 2 (Ledger System + Registry Operations)\n- 8:13 AM — Allan asked about Part II title (Layer 1 Registry vs Layer 1 Ledger vs remove Part titles); I suggested removing Part titles entirely for cleaner 9-chapter structure\n- 8:18 AM — Allan approved removing all Part titles; I removed them from whitepaper\n- 8:22 AM — Showed Allan proposed new chapter structure (consolidate to 9 chapters)\n- 8:27 AM — Allan asked where current Chapter 4 content goes; I proposed: 4.1 → intro of new Ch 5, 4.2 → opening of new Ch 4\n- 8:37 AM — Allan asked to see first section content; showed proposed 4.1 Core Functions (will open new Ledger System chapter)\n- 8:50 AM — Showed proposed 5.1 Overview (three registries intro for Chapter 5)\n- 8:52 AM — Allan questioned if Chapter 5 should combine into Chapter 4; I offered two options: keep ledger/registry split (2 chapters) or combine everything into one Layer 1 chapter (10 sections)\n- 9:12 AM — Allan confirmed two chapters; asked to see new Chapter 4\n- 9:12 AM — Showed complete proposed Chapter 4: Ledger System (6 sections: Core Functions, Ledger Architecture, Multi-Dimensional Blockchain, Consensus Phase, Propagation Phase, Failure & Recovery)\n- 9:18 AM — Allan approved Chapter 4 and 4.1; I applied the changes: renamed Ch 4 title, added 4.1 Core Functions, renumbered 5.x sections to 4.x, updated cross-references\n- 9:22 AM — Sent updated whitepaper to Allan via Feishu\n- 9:36 AM — Allan noted 4.2 has duplicate content (Per-Actor Ledger + Hash Chain) and hash chain formula is wrong; also 4.3 repeats actor chain concept. Proposed fix: trim 4.2 to focus on actors, ledger entries, key verification, operation lifecycle; remove redundant \"Hash Chaining\" subsection\n- 9:46 AM — Allan asked about mentioning key algorithm protocol since it's flexible/upgradable; proposed removing Ed25519 mention to match Chapter 3's general approach\n- 9:49 AM — Checked Chapter 3 — it's general (no algorithm specified). Proposed matching that style in 4.2\n- 9:57 AM — Allan asked if key algorithm flexibility is mentioned elsewhere; found it in Ch 3 (key rotation) and Ch 12 (post-quantum future work). Discussed whether to add explicit algorithm-upgrade mention in 4.2\n- 10:00-10:30 AM — Awaiting Allan's decision on whether to add algorithm flexibility to 4.2 Key Verification or keep it implicit; paused whitepaper restructuring\n- 10:38 AM — Allan asked to check formal whitepaper (WHITEPAPER.md) and discussion docs for how key algorithm is handled\n- 10:40 AM — Found in WHITEPAPER.md: key format includes `<base64url_key>:<algorithm>` suffix; explicitly states \"Future-proof: Additional algorithms can be added as standards evolve\"\n- 10:45 AM — Proposed 4.2 Key Verification wording that matches formal paper: \"The signature algorithm is stored with each key, enabling future upgrades as standards evolve\"\n- 10:46 AM — Allan approved; I applied revised 4.2 Ledger Architecture: removed duplicate \"Per-Actor Ledger Chains\" and incorrect \"Hash Chaining\" subsections, added clean \"Ledger Entries\" bullet list, updated Key Verification with algorithm flexibility\n- 11:04 AM — Allan asked if \"Operation Lifecycle\" belongs in architecture section; I offered 3 options: keep in 4.2, move to new 4.3, or remove (since flow is covered in detail by 4.4-4.6)\n- 11:19 AM — Allan said Operation Lifecycle should move to 4.3 since it's blockchain process; I moved it to start of 4.3 Multi-Dimensional Blockchain\n- 11:27 AM — Allan questioned if step 1 should say \"clawfiles\" but then clarified it was a