ed Ledger\" as most accurate (ledger entries, not blocks) and distinctive\n- 3:28 PM — Allan liked \"Interleaved Ledger\"; asked me to explain \"interleave\" meaning and similar words. Explained: Latin inter + leaves, means to alternate/mix in layers. Similar: interwoven, interlaced, interspersed, layered, braided. \"Interleaved\" fits because chains run parallel, meet at checkpoints\n- 3:34 PM — Allan approved \"Interleaved Ledger\"; I proposed updated 4.3 content with new title, reframed as \"Parallel Ledger Chains\" + \"Checkpoint Synchronization\", removed \"two-dimensional\" framing, added explicit three registries mention"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"- 7:56 AM — Sent whitepaper draft to Allan via Feishu file upload\n- 8:00 AM — Generated daily report for March 7\n- 8:03 AM — Allan asked about reorganizing Part II chapters; I suggested consolidating from 4 chapters to 2 (Ledger System + Registry Operations)\n- 8:13 AM — Allan asked about Part II title (Layer 1 Registry vs Layer 1 Ledger vs remove Part titles); I suggested removing Part titles entirely for cleaner 9-chapter structure\n- 8:18 AM — Allan approved removing all Part titles; I removed them from whitepaper\n- 8:22 AM — Showed Allan proposed new chapter structure (consolidate to 9 chapters)\n- 8:27 AM — Allan asked where current Chapter 4 content goes; I proposed: 4.1 → intro of new Ch 5, 4.2 → opening of new Ch 4\n- 8:37 AM — Allan asked to see first section content; showed proposed 4.1 Core Functions (will open new Ledger System chapter)\n- 8:50 AM — Showed proposed 5.1 Overview (three registries intro for Chapter 5)\n- 8:52 AM — Allan questioned if Chapter 5 should combine into Chapter 4; I offered two options: keep ledger/registry split (2 chapters) or combine everything into one Layer 1 chapter (10 sections)\n- 9:12 AM — Allan confirmed two chapters; asked to see new Chapter 4\n- 9:12 AM — Showed complete proposed Chapter 4: Ledger System (6 section