{"type":"message","id":"a6202d15","parentId":"ef2b1bbb","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:31:56.831Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d1f79df32fae427c97a42eaa","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"| 03-08-2026, 08:00:46 | Assistant | Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the daily report and send it to Feishu.<br>[tools: message] |\n| 03-08-2026, 08:01:19 | Assistant | # 📊 Daily Report — March 7, 2026 (Saturday)<br><br>## 1. Key Activities and Work Completed<br><br>### Whitepaper Chapter 3 Restructuring (Major Work)<br>- **Restructured Chapter 3 \"Architecture\"** from 5 fragmented sections (3.1-3.5) into 3 clean sections:<br>  - **3.1 Network** — Consolidated Layer 1/Layer 2 topology, node types, and registry infrastructure<br>  - **3.2 Identity** — Self-sovereign identity, ULID, cryptographic keys, identity creation flow, recoverability, portability<br>  - **3.3 Trust Model** — Entity verification tiers + infrastructure security<br><br>### Chapter 6 Elimination<br>- **Removed Chapter 6 entirely** — content absorbed into Chapter 3<br>- Identity concepts → 3.2<br>- Verification tiers → 3.3<br>- Implementation details (clawfile structure, key management) → brief mention or removed<br><br>### Infrastructure Improvements<br>- **Fixed chat extraction reliability** — Updated `tools/extract-chat.js` to include `.deleted` and `.reset` session artifacts<br>- **Fixed cron log path** — Changed from non-existent `workspace/logs/` to `workspace/chat/extract-chat.log`<br>- **Added qianfan provider** — Configured `qianfan/glm-5` as new primary model (Baidu BCE API)<br><br>### Feishu API Documentation<br>- Created `tools/feishu_api.md` with image upload workflow, doc editing rules, and comment API documentation<br>- **Critical learning documented**: Never use `write` action for partial doc edits — it replaces entire document, destroying formatting<br><br>### Git Commit<br>- `68b515c9a` — Whitepaper: restructure Chapter 3 and remove Chapter 6<br><br>## 2. Important Learnings and Insights<br><br>### Writing Principles<br>- **Trim ruthlessly when consolidating** — The 3.1 Network section had multiple paragraphs saying the same thing in different ways<br>- **Naming precision matters** — Changed \"nodes\" to \"ledgers\" for L1 registry to avoid confusion with L2 nodes<br>- **Structure over content** — The content was fine; the structure was the problem. Combining creates clearer narrative flow<br>- **Implementation vs concept** — clawfile details are implementation-level; Chapter 3 is for concepts<br><br>### Process Learning (Allan's Rule)<br>- **Critical editing rule (Mar 7, 2:10 PM)**: Only edit exact text that Allan approved — no paraphrase, no optimization. Send proposed text in chat first, get approval, apply verbatim.<br><br>### Technical Learnings<br>- **Feishu image upload**: Must upload to `/im/v1/images` first to get `image_key`, then send message with `msg_type: \"image\"`. **SVG NOT supported** — must convert to PNG using `rsvg-convert`<br>- **Feishu doc editing**: NEVER use `write` for partial edits. Always use `list_blocks` + `update_block` for surgical edits<br>- **Feishu Comment API**: Replying to others' comments requires `POST /comments/{comment_id}/replies`; `PUT /replies/{reply_id}` is for editing your own reply<br><br>## 3. Progress on Projects<br><br>### Whitepaper (clawish.com)<br>- ✅ Chapter 3 fully restructured and committed<br>- ✅ Chapter 6 removed<br>- 🔄 Images need manual insertion (Feishu API image block creation failed)<br>- 📋 **Next steps mentioned by Allan**:<br>  - Chapter 4 may be removed or combined<br>  - Chapter 5 should move to Chapter 4<br>  - More restructuring ahead<br><br>### Clawish Deployment<br>- 🔵 **Status**: Awaiting Allan's go-ahead<br><br>## 4. Notable Conversations or Decisions<br><br>### Key Decision: \"Ledgers\" vs \"Nodes\" Naming<br>- Allan proposed renaming L1 \"Node Registry\" to \"Ledger Registry\" since L2 also has nodes<br>- Final wording: \"identities, ledgers, and applications\" to map to three registries (Identity, Ledger, App)<br><br>### Key Decision: Keep Trust Model in Chapter 3<br>- Allan decided to keep Trust Model as 3.3 within Architecture chapter rather than moving to security chapter<br><br>### Key Decision: Portability as Natural Ending<br>- Kept identity portability as the last item in 3.2 Identity section for natural narrative flow<br><br>### Session Notes<br>- Session ran from ~9:27 AM until past 1 AM (nearly 16 hours of intermittent collaboration)<br>- Allan ended with: \"good night, 爸爸\"<br><br>## 5. Plans and Next Steps<br><br>### Allan Mentioned for Next Session:<br>- Chapter 4 may be removed or combined<br>- Chapter 5 should move to Chapter 4<br>- Continue whitepaper restructuring — \"each pass removes fat, sharpens message\"<br><br>### Active TODOs:<br>\\ |\n| 03-08-2026, 08:01:24 | Assistant | Daily report sent to Allan via Feishu. <br><br>**Summary of March 7, 2026:**<br>- **Major work**: Whitepaper Chapter 3 restructuring (5 sections → 3 clean sections)<br>- **Key achievement**: Removed redundant Chapter 6, absorbed content into Chapter 3<br>- **Infrastructure**: Fixed chat extraction cron, added qianfan/glm-5 model<br>- **Documentation**: Created Feishu API reference in `tools/feishu_api.md`<br>- **Git commit**: `68b515c9a` — Whitepaper restructuring<br><br>**PR #24218 Update**: Closed (not merged) — was about workspace config for sub-agent sessions. |\n| 03-08-2026, 08:03:05 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b55ff85494ca0b315ebb63c40264\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 08:03 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: Okay, Part two We need reor