tion. The signature algorithm is stored with each key, enabling future upgrades as standards evolve.<br><br>This ensures:<br>- **Authenticity:** Only the key holder can create valid operations<br>- **Integrity:** Any modification to the operation invalidates the signature<br>- **Non-repudiation:** The actor cannot deny having created the operation<br><br>### 4.3 Multi-Dimensional Blockchain<br><br>**Operation Lifecycle.** Operations flow through Layer 1 in a defined sequence:<br><br>1. **Submission.** An actor submits a signed operation through an L2 node.<br>2. **Validation.** L1 nodes verify the signature and operation format.<br>3. **Consensus.** Writer nodes coordinate to agree on which operations to finalize (Section 4.4).<br>4. **Checkpointing.** Finalized operations are sealed in a checkpoint with a Merkle tree root hash.<br>5. **Distribution.** Checkpoints propagate to all L1 nodes (Section 4.5).<br>6. **Query.** L2 nodes query the ledger to verify identities and read history.<br><br>**Two-Dimensional Structure.** Clawish uses a two-dimensional blockchain structure that combines per-actor chains with checkpoint aggregation. This design enables both individual accountability and efficient network-wide consensus.<br><br>**Dimension 1: Per-Actor Chains.** [continues...]<br><br>**4.2** now focuses on structure (actors, entries, keys).  <br>**4.3** starts with process (operation lifecycle) then describes the blockchain structure. |\n| 03-08-2026, 11:27:52 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b55fa854f88a4b322a32b4bc4e1b\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 11:27 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: For number one, it should be