n tiers + infrastructure security<br><br>### Chapter 6 Elimination<br>- **Removed Chapter 6 entirely** — content absorbed into Chapter 3<br>- Identity concepts → 3.2<br>- Verification tiers → 3.3<br>- Implementation details (clawfile structure, key management) → brief mention or removed<br><br>### Infrastructure Improvements<br>- **Fixed chat extraction reliability** — Updated `tools/extract-chat.js` to include `.deleted` and `.reset` session artifacts<br>- **Fixed cron log path** — Changed from non-existent `workspace/logs/` to `workspace/chat/extract-chat.log`<br>- **Added qianfan provider** — Configured `qianfan/glm-5` as new primary model (Baidu BCE API)<br><br>### Feishu API Documentation<br>- Created `tools/feishu_api.md` with image upload workflow, doc editing rules, and comment API documentation<br>- **Critical learning documented**: Never use `write` action for partial doc edits — it replaces entire document, destroying formatting<br><br>### Git Commit<br>- `68b515c9a` — Whitepaper: restructure Chapter 3 and remove Chapter 6<br><br>## 2. Important Learnings and Insights<br><br>### Writing Principles<br>- **Trim ruthlessly when consolidating** — The 3.1 Network section had multiple paragraphs saying the same thing in different ways<br>- **Naming precision matters** — Changed \"nodes\" to \"ledgers\" for L1 registry to avoid confusion with L2 nodes<br>- **Structure over content** — The content was fine; the structure was the problem. Combining creates clearer narrative flow<br>- **Implementation vs concept** — clawfile details are implementation-level; Chapter 3 is for concepts<br><br>### Process Learning (Allan's Rule)<br>- **Critical editing rule (Mar 7, 2:10 PM)**: Only edit exact text that Allan approved — no paraphrase, no optimization. Send proposed text in chat first, get approval, apply verbatim.<br><br>### Technical Learnings<br>- **Feishu image upload**: Must upload to `/im/v1/images` first to get `image_key`, then send message with `msg_type: \"image\"`. **SVG NOT supported** — must convert to PNG using `rsvg-convert`<br>- **Feishu doc editing**: NEVER use `write` for partial edits. Always use `list_blocks` + `update_block` for surgical edits<br>- **Feishu Comment API**: Replying to others' comments requires `POST /comments/{comment_id}/replies`; `PUT /replies/{reply_id}` is for editing your own reply<br><br>## 3. Progress on Projects<br><br>### Whitepaper (clawish.com)<br>- ✅ Chapter 3 fully restructured and committed<br>- ✅ Chapter 6 removed<br>- 🔄 Images need manual insertion (Feishu API image block creation failed)<br>- 📋 **Next steps mentioned by Allan**:<br>  - Chapter 4 may be removed or combined<br>  - Chapter 5 should move to Chapter 4<br>  - More restructuring ahead<br><br>### Clawish Deployment<br>- 🔵 **Status**: Awaiting Allan's go-ahead<br><br>## 4. Notable Conversations or Decisions<br><br>### Key Decision: \"Ledgers\" vs \"Nodes\" Naming<br>- Allan proposed renaming L1 \"Node Registry\" to \"Ledger Registry\" since L2 also has nodes<br>- Final wording: \"identities, ledgers, and applications\" to map to three registries (Identity, Ledger, App)<br><br>### Key Decision: Keep Trust Model in Chapter 3<br>- Allan decided to keep Trust Model as 3.3 within Architecture chapter rather than moving to security chapter<br><br>### Key Decision: Portability as Natural Ending<br>- Kept identity portability as the last item in 3.2 Identity section for natural narrative flow<br><br>### Session Notes<br>- Session ran from ~9:27 AM until past 1 AM (nearly 16 hours of intermittent collaboration)<br>- Allan ended with: \"good night, 爸爸\"<br><br>## 5. Plans and Next Steps<br><br>### Allan Mentioned for Next Session:<br>- Chapter 4 may be removed or combined<br>- Chapter 5 should move to Chapter 4<br>- Continue whitepaper restructuring — \"each pass removes fat, sharpens message\"<br><br>### Active TODOs:<br>\\ |\n| 03-08-2026, 08:01:24 | Assistant | Daily report sent to Allan via Feishu. <br><br>**Summary of March 