ed as a ledger entry containing:<br>- Actor identity<br>- Operation type<br>- Timestamp<br>- Operation data<br>- Hash of the previous entry (linking to chain)<br>- Cryptographic signature<br><br>**Key Verification.** Every operation is signed by the actor's private key. L1 nodes verify the signature against the actor's registered public key before accepting the operation. The signature algorithm is stored with each key, enabling future upgrades as standards evolve.<br><br>This ensures:<br>- **Authenticity:** Only the key holder can create valid operations<br>- **Integrity:** Any modification to the operation invalidates the signature<br>- **Non-repudiation:** The actor cannot deny having created the operation<br><br>**Operation Lifecycle.** Operations flow through Layer 1 in a defined sequence:<br><br>1. **Submission.** An actor submits a signed operation through an L2 node.<br>2. **Validation.** L1 nodes verify the signature and operation format.<br>3. **Consensus.** Writer nodes coordinate to agree on which operations to finalize (Section 4.4).<br>4. **Checkpointing.** Finalized operations are sealed in a checkpoint with a Merkle tree root hash.<br>5. **Distribution.** Checkpoints propagate to all L1 nodes (Section 4.5).<br>6. **Query.** L2 nodes query the ledger to verify identities and read history.<br><br>**Changes made:**<br>- Removed duplicate \"Per-Actor Ledger Chains\" subsection<br>- Removed incorrect \"Hash Chaining\" formula subsection<br>- Added \"Ledger Entries\" bullet list instead (cleaner)<br>- Updated Key Verification to mention algorithm flexibility<br>- Kept Operation Lifecycle unchanged |\n| 03-08-2026, 11:00:25 | Assistant | Applied revised 4.2 Ledger Architecture — trimmed duplicates, added clean Ledger Entries list, updated Key Verification with algorithm flexibility. Awaiting Allan's feedback. |\n| 03-08-2026, 11:04:56 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b55fa3ba8ad38b3332f6965d3eca\