                 │                 │<br>    │ SEAL            │ SEAL            │ SEAL<br>    │ (sign)          │ (sign)          │ (sign)<br>    │                 │                 │<br>    └────────┬────────┴────────┬────────┘<br>             │                 │<br>             └────────┬────────┘<br>                      ▼<br>              CHECKPOINT FINALIZED<br>```<br><br>Do you want me to create this diagram? Should I make it simple (first version) or detailed (multi-writer view)? |\n| 03-08-2026, 17:46:56 | Assistant | Showed Allan two 5-stage diagram options: simple linear flow (COMMIT→SUBMIT→MERGE→COMPARE→SEAL) or detailed multi-writer view with writers coordinating at each stage. Awaiting his preference on which to create. |\n| 03-08-2026, 17:51:24 | Assistant | consensus-five-stages.png |\n| 03-08-2026, 17:53:19 | Assistant | Created and sent the 5-stage consensus diagram! 🦞<br><br>**consensus-five-stages.png** shows:<br>- **COMMIT** (green, local) — Collect pending operations<br>- **SUBMIT** (orange, network) — Broadcast to other writers<br>- **MERGE** (blue, local) — Unify operations from all writers<br>- **COMPARE** (pink, network) — Verify all have same set<br>- **SEAL** (purple, network) — Sign checkpoint, finalize<br><br>Each stage is color-coded with description and local/network label. Flow ends with \"CHECKPOINT FINALIZED.\"<br><br>Should I add this diagram to the whitepaper 4.4? |\n| 03-08-2026, 18:00:54 | Assistant | Created 5-stage consensus diagram (consensus-five-stages.png) — color-coded horizontal flow showing COMMIT→SUBMIT→MERGE→COMPARE→SEAL with local/network labels. Sent to Allan for review, awaiting feedback before adding to whitepaper. |\n| 03-08-2026, 18:07:57 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b55e0e979a0a0b24a6bfacef6340\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Sun 2026-03-08 18:07 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<b