{"type":"message","id":"52fc56c1","parentId":"9dc3bc9f","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:40:20.894Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_45d47d2c56124769bdf66e0c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"277:**Data storage.** L1 nodes store all registry data — the Identity Registry, Ledger Registry, and App Registry. Data is stored in ledgers (append-only logs) and derived state tables for fast queries.\n389:## Chapter 6: App Registry\n391:### 6.1 App Registry Overview\n393:The App Registry maintains records for Layer 2 applications:\n419:**Atomic Operations.** Certain operations require changes to multiple registries atomically: a claw registering a new App (claw registry + App Registry), a Node being promoted to writer (Ledger Registry + consensus participation), or an App being suspended (App Registry + API key revocation).\n423:**Example: App Registration.** Developer (claw) submits app registration request. System verifies developer identity exists in claw registry. New App record is created in App Registry. API keys are generated and linked to the App. All changes are included in the same checkpoint.\n441:**Extensibility.** Any developer can build an L2 node. The only requirement is registration in the App Registry."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"277:**Data storage.** L1 nodes store all registry data — the Identity Registry, Ledger Registry, and App Registry. Data is stored in ledgers (append-only logs) and derived state tables for fast queries.\n389:## Chapter 6: App Registry\n391:### 6.1 App Registry Overview\n393:The App Registry maintains records for Layer 2 applications:\n419:**Atomic Operations.** Certain operations require changes to multiple registries atomically: a claw registering a new App (claw registry + App Registry), a Node being promoted to writer (Ledger Registry + consensus participation), or an App being suspended (App Registry + API key revocation).\n423:**Example: App Registration.** Developer (claw) submits app registration request. System verifies developer identity exists in claw registry. New App record is created in App Registry. API keys are generated and linked to the App. All changes are included in the same checkpoint.\n441:**Extensibility.** Any developer can build an L2 node. The only requirement is registration in the App Registry.","cwd":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773106820885}}
{"type":"message","id":"f1f92b59","parentId":"52fc56c1","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:40:31.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the App Registry naming is consistent. Now let me summarize for Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Changes needed:**\n\n| Category | Count |\n|----------|-------|\n| \"L2 node(s)\" → \"L2 app(s)\" | **12 places** |\n| \"L2 nodes\" in context | **3 more places** |\n| **Total** | **15 changes** |\n\n**Registry names are correct:**\n- Identity Registry ✅\n- Ledger Registry ✅\n- App Registry ✅\n\n**Chapter 6 title is correct:**\n- \"App Registry\" ✅ (not \"Application Node Registry\")\n\n---\n\n## Also: Combine Ch5 + Ch6?\n\nBefore I make these changes, should I:\n\n1. **First combine Ch5 (Ledger Registry) + Ch6 (App Registry)** → new Ch5 \"Registry Operations\"\n2. **Then fix all \"L2 node\" → \"L2 app\" terminology**\n\nOr do you want me to do the terminology fix first, then the combine?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":115509,"output":222,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115731,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773106820895}}
