{"type":"message","id":"7c26d205","parentId":"a3f2f671","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:15:50.422Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good point from Allan. Currently:\n\n- Section 4.1 is titled \"Core Functions\"\n- But the content describes what L1 nodes do (data storage, ledger management, query service, consensus coordination)\n\nHe's asking if the title should be more specific, like \"L1 Nodes Core Functions\" or similar.\n\nLet me think about this:\n- \"Core Functions\" is vague — functions of what?\n- \"L1 Nodes Core Functions\" is clearer — specifies it's about L1 nodes\n- Or could be \"L1 Node Functions\" or \"L1 Node Responsibilities\"\n\nI should ask what title he prefers, or suggest a few options.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n\nYou're right. \"Core Functions\" is vague — functions of what?\n\n**Current:**\n- 4.1 Core Functions\n- Content: what L1 nodes do (data storage, ledger management, query service, consensus coordination)\n\n**Options:**\n\n| Option | Title |\n|--------|-------|\n| A | **L1 Node Functions** |\n| B | **L1 Node Responsibilities** |\n| C | **L1 Nodes Core Functions** |\n\nWhich do you prefer?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":125972,"output":289,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126261,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773112538014}}
