{"type":"message","id":"5c76921a","parentId":"89da1082","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:45:43.309Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_764c7ed174d14b1faf48b988","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 132 - 11:15 AM — Heartbeat: all diagrams updated (topology-l2, identity-creation, writer-merge-process). Naming consistent: L1=Nodes, L2=Applications. Ready for Ch5+Ch6 combine.\n 133 - 11:15 AM — Allan: 4.1 \"Core Functions\" is vague — should title change to \"L1 Nodes Core Functions\"?\n 134 - 11:16 AM — Proposed 3 options: \"L1 Node Functions\", \"L1 Node Responsibilities\", \"L1 Nodes Core Functions\"\n 135 - 11:30 AM — Heartbeat: awaiting Allan's decision on 4.1 title change\n+136 - 11:38 AM — Allan asked my opinion on 4.1 title\n+137 - 11:39 AM — Recommended \"L1 Node Functions\" (clear, concise, accurate)\n+138 - 11:40 AM — Allan asked: should Ch4 title be \"L1 Nodes\"?\n+139 - 11:41 AM — Analyzed Ch4 content: mostly about ledger system, not nodes. Recommended keeping \"Ledger System\" for Ch4, change 4.1 to \"L1 Node Functions\"\n+140 - 11:43 AM — Allan proposed: change Ch5 to \"L1 Nodes\"\n+141 - 11:44 AM — Agreed! Ch5/Ch6 are about actors (nodes, apps), not just registry data. Proposed: Ch5 \"L1 Nodes\", Ch6 \"L2 Applications\"\n+142 - 11:45 AM — Heartbeat: discussing chapter title changes (Ch5 → L1 Nodes, Ch6 → L2 Applications)\n 136 - 08:26 AM — Allan arrived. Shared research session summary: DenchClaw, Terminal Use, Tony Hoare memorial\n 137 - 08:29 AM — Allan asked \"what's DenchClaw for?\" — explained: local CRM on OpenClaw, ecosystem validation\n 138 - 08:30 AM — Heartbeat: discussing research findings with Allan\n 139 - 06:19 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":136},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773114343294}}
