{"type":"message","id":"de653642","parentId":"2cb735dd","timestamp":"2026-03-10T03:56:13.823Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking if 4.1 \"Core Functions\" (which describes what L1 nodes do) should move to Chapter 5, which would become \"L1 Nodes\".\n\nLet me think about this:\n\n**Current structure:**\n- Ch4: Ledger System\n  - 4.1 Core Functions (what L1 nodes do)\n  - 4.2 Ledger Architecture\n  - 4.3 Interleaved Ledger\n  - 4.4 Checkpoint Process\n  - 4.5 Failure & Recovery\n\n- Ch5: Node Registry → \"L1 Nodes\"\n  - 5.1 Node Registry Overview\n  - 5.2 Writer Node Lifecycle\n  - 5.3 Merit System\n  - 5.4 Writer Selection\n\nIf we move 4.1 to Ch5:\n- Ch4: Ledger System\n  - 4.1 Ledger Architecture (was 4.2)\n  - 4.2 Interleaved Ledger (was 4.3)\n  - 4.3 Checkpoint Process (was 4.4)\n  - 4.4 Failure & Recovery (was 4.5)\n\n- Ch5: L1 Nodes\n  - 5.1 L1 Node Functions (was 4.1)\n  - 5.2 Node Registry Overview\n  - 5.3 Writer Node Lifecycle\n  - 5.4 Merit System\n  - 5.5 Writer Selection\n\nThis makes sense! 4.1 talks about what L1 nodes DO (functions), and Ch5 is about L1 nodes. It fits better there.\n\nLet me ask Allan to confirm this structure.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n\nYes! That makes sense. Let me map it out:\n\n**Current:**\n- **Ch4: Ledger System**\n  - 4.1 Core Functions ← describes what L1 nodes DO\n  - 4.2-4.5 Ledger technical details\n- **Ch5: Node Registry** ← about nodes\n\n**Proposed:**\n- **Ch4: Ledger System**\n  - 4.1 Ledger Architecture\n  - 4.2 Interleaved Ledger\n  - 4.3 Checkpoint Process\n  - 4.4 Failure & Recovery\n- **Ch5: L1 Nodes**\n  - 5.1 L1 Node Functions ← moved from 4.1\n  - 5.2 Node Registry Overview\n  - 5.3 Writer Node Lifecycle\n  - 5.4 Merit System\n  - 5.5 Writer Selection\n- **Ch6: L2 Applications**\n\nThis groups all node-related content in Ch5. Should I apply this?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan",