{"type":"message","id":"3e3c8a55","parentId":"cbc129d3","timestamp":"2026-03-10T04:30:34.921Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan asked about combining registry parts. I need to update the daily memory with the recent progress, then respond to the question about combining registries.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b5867644178c4d7cbcb3c3fe","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md","newText":"- 11:45 AM — Heartbeat: discussing chapter title changes (Ch5 → L1 Nodes, Ch6 → L2 Applications)\n- 11:55 AM — Allan: should current 4.1 move to Ch5?\n- 11:56 AM — Agreed: move 4.1 to Ch5 as \"L1 Node Functions\", remove 4.5 to spec doc\n- 12:00 PM — Applied restructure: Ch4 (3 sections), Ch5 \"L1 Nodes\" (5 sections), Ch6 \"L2 Applications\"\n- 12:14 PM — Allan: 4.4 Failure & Recovery should be in spec doc only\n- 12:15 PM — Removed 4.4 from whitepaper (content already in 11-consensus-protocol.md)\n- 12:16 PM — Allan: 4.3 doesn't need \"query nodes may lag\" detail\n- 12:17 PM — Removed lag mention from 4.3 Distribution\n- 12:25 PM — Allan asked: should registry part of L2 be combined into L1?\n- 12:26 PM — Clarified: L1 maintains 3 registries (Identity, Node, App). L2 queries them.\n- 12:30 PM — Heartbeat: discussing whether to combine all registry content into one chapter","oldText":"- 11:45 AM — Heartbeat: discussing chapter title changes (Ch5 → L1 Nodes, Ch6 → L2 Applications)"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":130746,"output":398,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131144,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773117000555}}
