stries) in ledgers and derived state tables, verify signed operations, record them to the appropriate ledgers, and serve query requests from L2 applications.\"\n+168 - 13:30 PM — Heartbeat: working on 3.1 Network rewrite, awaiting approval on proposed one-sentence functions description\n 153 - 08:26 AM — Allan arrived. Shared research session summary: DenchClaw, Terminal Use, Tony Hoare memorial\n 154 - 08:29 AM — Allan asked \"what's DenchClaw for?\" — explained: local CRM on OpenClaw, ecosystem validation\n 155 - 08:30 AM — Heartbeat: discussing research findings with Allan\n 156 - 06:19 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":153},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773120645397}}
