{"type":"message","id":"c3398473","parentId":"caa63a47","timestamp":"2026-03-10T05:49:15.102Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants to see proposed 4.4 text. Let me read current Ch5 sections (Writer Node Lifecycle, Merit System, Writer Selection) and rewrite them as 4.4 for Ch4.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f5b1e7a1a7824c959f8e8eaf","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","limit":30,"offset":315}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":121859,"output":106,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121965,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773121716986}}
{"type":"message","id":"552aebff","parentId":"c3398473","timestamp":"2026-03-10T05:49:15.129Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f5b1e7a1a7824c959f8e8eaf","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- **SUBMIT.** Writers broadcast their pending operations to other writers.\n- **MERGE.** Each writer merges received operations into a unified ledger set.\n- **COMPARE.** Writers compare their merged ledger sets to ensure agreement.\n- **SEAL.** Writers sign the checkpoint and exchange signatures.\n\n![Checkpoint Consensus Protocol](consensus-checkpoint-overview.png)\n\nAll writers sign simultaneously rather than in sequence. Once a writer collects signatures from a quorum, the checkpoint is finalized with its round number, timestamp, Merkle root, and reference to the previous checkpoint.\n\n**Distribution.** Query nodes pull new checkpoints from writers to update their local ledger copies. They verify checkpoint signatures independently and apply the checkpoint to local ledgers.\n\n**Query.** Once synchronized, query nodes serve read requests from L2 apps: identity verification, ledger history, and checkpoint validation. Applications query the ledger to verify identities and read operation history.\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 5: L1 Nodes\n\n### 5.1 Node Registry Overview\n\nThe Node Registry maintains records for all infrastructure nodes:\n\n**Node Record Structure.** Each node record contains an identity_id (ULID) and public_key, node_type (Writer or Query), endpoint (network address), metrics (uptime percentage, response time, throughput, total rounds participated, successful rounds), merit_score (composite score for writer selection), status (Active, Inactive, or Suspended), and timestamps (created_at, updated_at).\n\n### 5.2 Writer Node Lifecycle\n\n1. **Registration.** Any claw can register as a node (initially as query node).\n2. **Probation.** New nodes operate in probation, building track record.\n3. **Promotion.** High-performing query nodes can be promoted to writer.\n4. **Active Service.** Writers participate in consensus and earn merit.\n5. **Demotion.** Underperforming writers are demoted to query nodes.\n\n[285 more lines in file. Use offset=345 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773121755114}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ad15e86","parentId":"552aebff","timestamp":"2026-03-10T05:49:57.294Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me get the rest of the writer content.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ae89827339014815a3a60bf5","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","limit":20,"offset":353}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":122359,"output":61,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":122420,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773121755130}}
{"type":"message","id":"9363304d","parentId":"4ad15e86","timestamp":"2026-03-10T05:49:57.325Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ae89827339014815a3a60bf5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"At each checkpoint round, the top N nodes by merit score are selected as writers. This ensures the most capable nodes maintain the ledger.\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 6: L2 Applications\n\n### 6.1 L2 Applications Overview\n\nThe L2 Applications Registry maintains records for Layer 2 applications:\n\n**App Record Structure.** Each app record contains an identity_id (ULID) and public_key, metadata (name, description, version, developer identity, website URL), api_keys (authenticated access keys), rate_limits (tier: Free/Standard/Premium), status (Active, Suspended, or Deprecated), and timestamps (created_at, updated_at).\n\n### 6.2 Registration Process\n\n1. **Create Identity.** Developer creates a claw identity for the app (or uses an existing one).\n2. **Submit Metadata.** Developer submits app metadata: name, description, version, developer info, website (optional), rate limit tier selection.\n3. **Receive API Keys.** The app receives API keys for authenticated access to Layer 1.\n4. **Rate Limits Assigned.** Based on tier selection (free, standard, premium).\n5. **Active.** The app is now active and can serve users.\n\n\n[257 more lines in file. Use offset=373 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773121797305}}
{"type":"message","id":"5afacc71","parentId":"9363304d","timestamp":"2026-03-10T05:50:54.503Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the writer content. Let me propose 4.4 that integrates writer lifecycle, merit, and selection. I need to rewrite it to fit within Ch4 (Ledger System) context, not just copy-paste.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n\n**Proposed 4.4 Writer Lifecycle & Selection:**\n\n---\n\n### 4.4 Writer Lifecycle & Selection\n\nWriter nodes are selected based on merit — a composite score reflecting their reliability and contribution to the network.\n\n**Merit Score.** Merit is calculated from multiple factors: uptime percentage, response time, throughput, and successful consensus participation. Higher scores indicate more reliable nodes.\n\n**Writer Selection.** At each checkpoint round, the top N nodes by merit score are selected as writers. This ensures the most capable nodes maintain the ledger and participate in consensus.\n\n**Lifecycle Stages.** Writer nodes progress through stages:\n\n1. **Registration.** Any claw can register as a node, initially as a query node.\n2. **Probation.** New nodes operate in probation, building a track record.\n3. **Promotion.** High-performing query nodes are promoted to writer status.\n4. **Active Service.** Writers participate in consensus and earn merit.\n5. **Demotion.** Underperforming writers are demoted back to query nodes.\n6. **Suspension.** Malicious or severely underperforming nodes are suspended.\n\nThis lifecycle ensures writers are proven, reliable participants while allowing new nodes to join and grow within the network.\n\n---\n\n**Changes from current:**\n1. Integrated merit, selection, and lifecycle into one cohesive section\n2. Rewrote for Ch4 context (part of ledger system)\n3. Removed Node Registry reference (that goes in Ch5 Registries)\n4. Flows naturally: what merit is → how writers are selected → lifecycle stages\n\nApprove?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":122683,"output":401,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123084,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773121797326}}
