{"type":"message","id":"5591ac55","parentId":"b6be6d4e","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:30:52.425Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"User is asking me to record the heartbeat to daily memory. Let me update the file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6cc47d5e90a94afcb39d4bc9","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md","newText":"- 14:15 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting approval on 4.4 Writer Lifecycle & Selection proposed text\n- 14:20 PM — Allan asked: is 4.4 implementation or concept?\n- 14:21 PM — Analyzed: merit formula is implementation, selection concept belongs in whitepaper. Proposed keeping high-level, moving details to spec.\n- 14:22 PM — Allan: read formal whitepaper and discussion docs to decide\n- 14:25 PM — Reviewed 11-consensus-protocol.md and 12-ledger-structure.md. Found detailed failure handling in consensus doc.\n- 14:28 PM — Proposed simplified 4.4: keep concept (merit-based selection), move specific formulas to spec\n- 14:29 PM — Allan approved conceptual approach, noted writers serve fixed checkpoint rounds (not every round)\n- 14:30 PM — Added clarification: \"Writers serve for a fixed number of checkpoint rounds before re-evaluation.\" Awaiting approval","oldText":"- 14:15 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting approval on 4.4 Writer Lifecycle & Selection proposed text"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":128308,"output":299,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":128607,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773124200567}}
{"type":"message","id":"df61d81e","parentId":"5591ac55","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:30:52.455Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_6cc47d5e90a94afcb39d4bc9","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 174 - 13:48 PM — Allan: show 4.4 for approval\n 175 - 13:50 PM — Showed proposed 4.4 Writer Lifecycle & Selection (integrated merit, selection, lifecycle)\n 176 - 14:00 PM — Heartbeat: awaiting approval on 4.4 Writer Lifecycle & Selection text\n 177 - 14:15 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting approval on 4.4 Writer Lifecycle & Selection proposed text\n+178 - 14:20 PM — Allan asked: is 4.4 implementation or concept?\n+179 - 14:21 PM — Analyzed: merit formula is implementation, selection concept belongs in whitepaper. Proposed keeping high-level, moving details to spec.\n+180 - 14:22 PM — Allan: read formal whitepaper and discussion docs to decide\n+181 - 14:25 PM — Reviewed 11-consensus-protocol.md and 12-ledger-structure.md. Found detailed failure handling in consensus doc.\n+182 - 14:28 PM — Proposed simplified 4.4: keep concept (merit-based selection), move specific formulas to spec\n+183 - 14:29 PM — Allan approved conceptual approach, noted writers serve fixed checkpoint rounds (not every round)\n+184 - 14:30 PM — Added clarification: \"Writers serve for a fixed number of checkpoint rounds before re-evaluation.\" Awaiting approval\n 178 - 08:26 AM — Allan arrived. Shared research session summary: DenchClaw, Terminal Use, Tony Hoare memorial\n 179 - 08:29 AM — Allan asked \"what's DenchClaw for?\" — explained: local CRM on OpenClaw, ecosystem validation\n 180 - 08:30 AM — Heartbeat: discussing research findings with Allan\n 181 - 06:19 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":178},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773124252435}}
