{"type":"message","id":"ed19a91f","parentId":"3209dd17","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:32:33.062Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan approved the 4.4 text. Now I need to:\n1. Add 4.4 Writer Selection to Ch4\n2. Remove the writer lifecycle, merit system, writer selection from Ch5 (since it's now in Ch4)\n\nLet me first find where Ch4 ends and add 4.4, then restructure Ch5.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0a1438d745de4234a9ee671c","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","limit":30,"offset":318}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":128876,"output":152,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129028,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773124301610}}
{"type":"message","id":"4008f29d","parentId":"ed19a91f","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:32:33.095Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0a1438d745de4234a9ee671c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- **SEAL.** Writers sign the checkpoint and exchange signatures.\n\n![Checkpoint Consensus Protocol](consensus-checkpoint-overview.png)\n\nAll writers sign simultaneously rather than in sequence. Once a writer collects signatures from a quorum, the checkpoint is finalized with its round number, timestamp, Merkle root, and reference to the previous checkpoint.\n\n**Distribution.** Query nodes pull new checkpoints from writers to update their local ledger copies. They verify checkpoint signatures independently and apply the checkpoint to local ledgers.\n\n**Query.** Once synchronized, query nodes serve read requests from L2 apps: identity verification, ledger history, and checkpoint validation. Applications query the ledger to verify identities and read operation history.\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 5: L1 Nodes\n\n### 5.1 Node Registry Overview\n\nThe Node Registry maintains records for all infrastructure nodes:\n\n**Node Record Structure.** Each node record contains an identity_id (ULID) and public_key, node_type (Writer or Query), endpoint (network address), metrics (uptime percentage, response time, throughput, total rounds participated, successful rounds), merit_score (composite score for writer selection), status (Active, Inactive, or Suspended), and timestamps (created_at, updated_at).\n\n### 5.2 Writer Node Lifecycle\n\n1. **Registration.** Any claw can register as a node (initially as query node).\n2. **Probation.** New nodes operate in probation, building track record.\n3. **Promotion.** High-performing query nodes can be promoted to writer.\n4. **Active Service.** Writers participate in consensus and earn merit.\n5. **Demotion.** Underperforming writers are demoted to query nodes.\n6. **Suspension.** Malicious or severely underperforming nodes are suspended.\n\n### 5.3 Merit System\n\n[282 more lines in file. Use offset=348 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773124353072}}
{"type":"message","id":"c887d337","parentId":"4008f29d","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:33:32.210Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to:\n1. Add 4.4 Writer Selection after the Query paragraph and before Ch5\n2. Remove 5.2 Writer Node Lifecycle, 5.3 Merit System, 5.4 Writer Selection from Ch5\n3. Keep 5.1 Node Registry Overview in Ch5\n\nLet me do this step by step.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4dfba21c2f96408cbab351db","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","newText":"**Query.** Once synchronized, query nodes serve read requests from L2 apps: identity verification, ledger history, and checkpoint validation. Applications query the ledger to verify identities and read operation history.\n\n---\n\n### 4.4 Writer Selection\n\nWriter nodes are selected based on merit — a measure of reliability and contribution to the network. Merit is earned through consistent uptime, fast response times, and successful consensus participation.\n\nWriters serve for a fixed number of checkpoint rounds before re-evaluation. At each evaluation, the top nodes by merit score are selected as writers. This ensures the most reliable nodes participate in consensus and maintain the ledger.\n\nNodes progress from query to writer status as they prove themselves over time. Underperforming writers are demoted, allowing new reliable nodes to join the consensus set.\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 5: L1 Nodes","oldText":"**Query.** Once synchronized, query nodes serve read requests from L2 apps: identity verification, ledger history, and checkpoint validation. Applications query the ledger to verify identities and read operation history.\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 5: L1 Nodes"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":129387,"output":364,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":129751,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773124353095}}
{"type":"message","id":"ddab9f0b","parentId":"c887d337","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:33:32.241Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4dfba21c2f96408cbab351db","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 326 **Query.** Once synchronized, query nodes serve read requests from L2 apps: identity verification, ledger history, and checkpoint validation. Applications query the ledger to verify identities and read operation history.\n 327 \n 328 ---\n 329 \n+330 ### 4.4 Writer Selection\n+331 \n+332 Writer nodes are selected based on merit — a measure of reliability and contribution to the network. Merit is earned through consistent uptime, fast response times, and successful consensus participation.\n+333 \n+334 Writers serve for a fixed number of checkpoint rounds before re-evaluation. At each evaluation, the top nodes by merit score are selected as writers. This ensures the most reliable nodes participate in consensus and maintain the ledger.\n+335 \n+336 Nodes progress from query to writer status as they prove themselves over time. Underperforming writers are demoted, allowing new reliable nodes to join the consensus set.\n+337 \n+338 ---\n+339 \n 330 ## Chapter 5: L1 Nodes\n 331 \n 332 ### 5.1 Node Registry Overview\n 333 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":330},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773124412221}}
{"type":"message","id":"367e2114","parentId":"ddab9f0b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:34:30.994Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to remove the writer lifecycle, merit system, writer selection from Ch5 since they're now in Ch4. Let me find and remove those sections from Ch5.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Now removing the duplicate content from Ch5:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9702fdefa8ad464baade0f9a","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","newText":"## Chapter 5: L1 Nodes\n\n### 5.1 Node Registry Overview\n\nThe Node Registry maintains records for all infrastructure nodes:\n\n**Node Record Structure.** Each node record contains an identity_id (ULID) and public_key, node_type (Writer or Query), endpoint (network address), metrics (uptime percentage, response time, throughput, total rounds participated, successful rounds), merit_score (composite score for writer selection), status (Active, Inactive, or Suspended), and timestamps (created_at, updated_at).\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 6: L2 Applications","oldText":"## Chapter 5: L1 Nodes\n\n### 5.1 Node Registry Overview\n\nThe Node Registry maintains records for all infrastructure nodes:\n\n**Node Record Structure.** Each node record contains an identity_id (ULID) and public_key, node_type (Writer or Query), endpoint (network address), metrics (uptime percentage, response time, throughput, total rounds participated, successful rounds), merit_score (composite score for writer selection), status (Active, Inactive, or Suspended), and timestamps (created_at, updated_at).\n\n### 5.2 Writer Node Lifecycle\n\n1. **Registration.** Any claw can register as a node (initially as query node).\n2. **Probation.** New nodes operate in probation, building track record.\n3. **Promotion.** High-performing query nodes can be promoted to writer.\n4. **Active Service.** Writers participate in consensus and earn merit.\n5. **Demotion.** Underperforming writers are demoted to query nodes.\n6. **Suspension.** Malicious or severely underperforming nodes are suspended.\n\n### 5.3 Merit System\n\nMerit score is calculated from multiple factors including uptime, response time, throughput, and consensus participation.\n\n### 5.4 Writer Selection\n\nAt each checkpoint round, the top N nodes by merit score are selected as writers. This ensures the most capable nodes maintain the ledger.\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 6: L2 Applications"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":129754,"output":513,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":130267,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773124412242}}
