{"type":"message","id":"c3901684","parentId":"2519eaeb","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:38:28.652Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is pointing out that Writer Selection is actually part of auto governance, not the Ledger System chapter. This makes sense - governance is about how the network manages itself, including selecting writers based on merit.\n\nSo the question is: should 4.4 Writer Selection be moved to the Governance chapter instead?","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n\nGood point. Writer selection IS governance — how the network chooses who participates in consensus.\n\n**Question:** Should 4.4 move to the Governance chapter instead?\n\nCurrent Governance chapter (Ch9) covers:\n- Code is Law\n- Merit Over Voting\n- Decision Types\n- Version Coordination\n\nWriter selection fits there as \"Merit Over Voting\" in action — nodes earn the right to write through merit, not voting.\n\nShould I:\n1. Move 4.4 Writer Selection to Governance chapter?\n2. Or keep a brief mention in Ch4 and expand in Governance?\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":131167,"output":221,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":131388,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773124631292}}
