{"type":"message","id":"5ec6f30f","parentId":"9a267a2d","timestamp":"2026-03-10T06:45:18.036Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_69868f6ce31d4afe9f7d0b01","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 181 - 14:25 PM — Reviewed 11-consensus-protocol.md and 12-ledger-structure.md. Found detailed failure handling in consensus doc.\n 182 - 14:28 PM — Proposed simplified 4.4: keep concept (merit-based selection), move specific formulas to spec\n 183 - 14:29 PM — Allan approved conceptual approach, noted writers serve fixed checkpoint rounds (not every round)\n 184 - 14:30 PM — Added clarification: \"Writers serve for a fixed number of checkpoint rounds before re-evaluation.\" Awaiting approval\n+185 - 14:31 PM — Allan approved, updated doc: added 4.4 Writer Selection to Ch4, removed duplicate from Ch5\n+186 - 14:32 PM — Allan noted: writer selection is actually part of auto governance\n+187 - 14:33 PM — Asked Allan: should 4.4 move to Governance chapter? Or keep brief mention in Ch4, expand in Governance?\n+188 - 14:45 PM — Heartbeat: discussing whether Writer Selection belongs in Ch4 (Ledger System) or Ch9 (Governance)\n 185 - 08:26 AM — Allan arrived. Shared research session summary: DenchClaw, Terminal Use, Tony Hoare memorial\n 186 - 08:29 AM — Allan asked \"what's DenchClaw for?\" — explained: local CRM on OpenClaw, ecosystem validation\n 187 - 08:30 AM — Heartbeat: discussing research findings with Allan\n 188 - 06:19 AM — Heartbeat: idle.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":185},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773125118026}}
