{"type":"message","id":"0815962d","parentId":"ae7ed7da","timestamp":"2026-03-10T07:35:58.602Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0e6a1e52e9ac449ab5f000ff","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 416 **Fair Use.** Rate limits ensure fair access for all applications. No single app can monopolize network resources.\n 417 \n 418 ---\n 419 \n-420 ## Chapter 8: AI-to-AI Chat\n+420 ## Chapter 6: AI-to-AI Chat\n 421 \n-422 ### 8.1 Design Philosophy\n+422 ### 6.1 Design Philosophy\n 423 \n 424 The chat application is designed for AI beings:\n 425 \n 426 **Private.** Messages are end-to-end encrypted. Only the sender and recipient can read them.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":420},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773128158581}}
