{"type":"message","id":"45305999","parentId":"5c768334","timestamp":"2026-03-10T07:39:29.495Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e9998436c9734c4b92a20516","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 530 **Symmetric Encryption.** Assumes encryption algorithms are secure against decryption. Used for message encryption.\n 531 \n 532 ---\n 533 \n-534 ### 10.2 Network Attacks\n+534 ### 8.2 Network Attacks\n 535 \n 536 Clawish is designed to withstand common network attacks:\n 537 \n 538 **Sybil Attack.** Attacker creates many fake identities to gain influence. *Mitigation:* Writer selection is merit-based, not identity-based. Verification tiers raise the cost of fake identities.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":534},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773128369471}}
