{"type":"message","id":"4e9db08d","parentId":"f57a37c9","timestamp":"2026-03-10T09:45:16.939Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_87c4a2b565cc4322a61731ac","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 221 - 17:06 PM — Allan approved: remove cross-registry mention\n 222 - 17:07 PM — Updated 3.3 Registry: removed cross-registry sentence, sent updated whitepaper\n 223 - 17:15 PM — Heartbeat: 3.3 Registry simplified. Whitepaper restructure complete — 8 chapters.\n 224 - 17:30 PM — Heartbeat: idle. Whitepaper restructure complete. Awaiting Allan's next steps.\n+225 - 17:32 PM — Allan: for 3.4 verification, do we need tier details? It's implementation.\n+226 - 17:33 PM — Found: 3.2 Identity already mentions Tier 0→Tier 1 (L2 temp → L1 permanent)\n+227 - 17:35 PM — Allan asked: does unverified vs verified difference need mention? It's different because T0 is L2 temporary, verified is L1 permanent\n+228 - 17:37 PM — Proposed: brief mention with L2 temp vs L1 permanent distinction, no detailed tiers\n+229 - 17:41 PM — Allan approved: brief mention is ok\n+230 - 17:42 PM — Updated 3.4 Entity Trust: simplified to one paragraph with key distinction\n+231 - 17:45 PM — Heartbeat: 3.4 Entity Trust simplified. Removed detailed tier definitions (implementation detail)\n 225 - 17:00 PM — Heartbeat: still awaiting Allan's approval on 3.3 Registry simplification\n 226 - 15:30 PM — Allan approved: use conceptual description (what), remove exact schema\n 227 - 15:31 PM — Added 3.3 Registry to Ch3 (three registries overview, brief)\n 228 - 15:32 PM — Removed old Ch5 (L1 Nodes) and Ch6 (L2 Applications), content moved to Ch3\n     ...","firstChangedLine":225},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773135916924}}
