{"type":"message","id":"37ed80a5","parentId":"aecfcab4","timestamp":"2026-03-10T10:57:26.240Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan likes Option 2 (simpler version) but wants to add a line about future algorithm being upgradable. Let me check if this is already mentioned somewhere else in the document.\n\nLooking at the current text:\n> **Key Verification.** Every operation is signed by the actor's private key. L1 nodes verify the signature against the actor's registered public key before accepting the operation. The signature algorithm is stored with each key, enabling future upgrades as standards evolve.\n\nSo the upgradability is already in the original text. I should keep that part.\n\nLet me combine the simpler version with the upgradability sentence.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n\nThe upgradability is already in the current text:\n\n> \"The signature algorithm is stored with each key, enabling future upgrades as standards evolve.\"\n\n**Proposed combined:**\n\n> **Key Verification.** Every operation is signed by the actor's private key. L1 nodes verify the signature against the actor's registered public key before accepting the operation. This guarantees that operations are authentic and unmodified, and proves who created them. The signature algorithm is stored with each key, enabling future upgrades as standards evolve.\n\nShould I update?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":138082,"output":295,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":138377,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773140180123}}
