{"type":"message","id":"8119811f","parentId":"4f26fbca","timestamp":"2026-03-10T11:24:22.958Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is saying:\n1. The previous paragraph (the simpler version without algorithm mention) is fine\n2. But he wants to add a sentence about algorithm being upgradeable\n3. The algorithm upgradability doesn't have to be tied to \"stored with each key\" - that's a different thing\n\nSo the structure should be:\n- Key verification paragraph (simpler version)\n- Separate sentence about algorithm upgradability (not tied to \"stored with key\")\n\nLet me write this:\n\n> **Key Verification.** Every operation is signed by the actor's private key. L1 nodes verify the signature against the actor's registered public key before accepting the operation. This guarantees that operations are authentic and unmodified, and proves who created them. Signature algorithms can be upgraded as standards evolve.\n\nThis separates the key verification concept from the algorithm upgradability concept.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n\nGot it. Separate the concepts:\n\n> **Key Verification.** Every operation is signed by the actor's private key. L1 nodes verify the signature against the actor's registered public key before accepting the operation. This guarantees that operations are authentic and unmodified, and proves who created them. Signature algorithms can be upgraded as standards evolve.\n\nShould I update?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":135381,"output":322,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135703,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773141803817}}
