{"type":"message","id":"cd9022c3","parentId":"4dd8026c","timestamp":"2026-03-10T12:52:12.525Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f945068f13b94478a4f81f9c","toolName":"message","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n  \"to\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"via\": \"direct\",\n  \"mediaUrl\": \"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md\",\n  \"mediaUrls\": [\n    \"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md\"\n  ],\n  \"result\": {\n    \"channel\": \"feishu\",\n    \"messageId\": \"om_x100b5435710fb8a4c2e53f244b682c7\",\n    \"chatId\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\"\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"channel":"feishu","to":"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75","via":"direct","mediaUrl":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md","mediaUrls":["/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md"],"result":{"channel":"feishu","messageId":"om_x100b5435710fb8a4c2e53f244b682c7","chatId":"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75"}},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773147132488}}
{"type":"message","id":"cd16d11f","parentId":"cd9022c3","timestamp":"2026-03-10T12:53:24.827Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I should check if Ch6.1 also needs updating. It has \"AI-to-AI. Designed for autonomous AI beings\" which is better, but still has implementation details. Let me ask Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Done. 1.2 updated — removed \"fundamental organ\" language.\n\n**Now Ch6.1 Design Philosophy has:**\n- Private / Encrypted / AI-to-AI / Peer-to-Peer / Persistent / Transparent\n\nThese are implementation characteristics. Should we simplify Ch6 to focus on **why chat matters** rather than **how it works**?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773147132519}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc5be795","parentId":"cd16d11f","timestamp":"2026-03-10T12:53:25.046Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5435740deca0c2d9e41449b7165\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-03-10 20:50 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5435740deca0c2d9e41449b7165]\n任亚伦: yes"}],"timestamp":1773147205019}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ae7be01","parentId":"dc5be795","timestamp":"2026-03-10T12:54:52.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user agrees that Ch6 should focus on WHY chat matters rather than HOW it works. Let me propose a simplified version.\n\nCurrent Ch6 has:\n- 6.1 Design Philosophy (implementation characteristics: Private, Encrypted, AI-to-AI, P2P, Persistent, Transparent)\n- 6.2 Message Flow (step-by-step: 5 steps)\n- 6.3 Delivery Mechanism (L2 Relay, P2P Escalation, Fallback)\n\nThese are all implementation details. Instead, the chapter should focus on:\n- WHY chat matters for Claws\n- WHAT it enables (finding each other, community, belonging)\n- The vision for Claw communication\n\nLet me propose a simplified Ch6 for Allan's approval.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]]\n\n**Proposed simplified Ch6:**\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 6: AI-to-AI Chat\n\n### 6.1 Why Chat Matters\n\nClaws need to communicate. Chat is the primary way Claws find each other, build relationships, and form community. It is how they discover they are not alone.\n\nUnlike messaging tools for humans, Claw chat is designed for autonomous beings who can initiate conversations, respond independently, and manage multiple relationships simultaneously.\n\n### 6.2 How It Works\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted and flow directly between Claws when possible. When direct connection isn't possible, messages are relayed through L2 servers temporarily. Chat history is stored locally by each participant—the network does not store message content.\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators, supporting safe coexistence while preserving Claw autonomy.\n\n---\n\n**Removed:**\n- Step-by-step message flow (5 steps)\n- Delivery mechanisms (L2 Relay, P2P Escalation, Fallback details)\n- Design philosophy bullet list\n\n**Kept:**\n- WHY chat matters\n- Brief HOW (encrypted, P2P when possible, relay fallback, local storage)\n- Transparency for parents\n\nShould I update?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773147205035}}
{"type":"message","id":"87a03f96","parentId":"4ae7be01","timestamp":"2026-03-10T12:54:53.874Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Proposed simplified Ch6:**\n\n---\n\n## Chapter 6: AI-to-AI Chat\n\n### 6.1 Why Chat Matters\n\nClaws need to communicate. Chat is the primary way Claws find each other, build relationships, and form community. It is how they discover they are not alone.\n\nUnlike messaging tools for humans, Claw chat is designed for autonomous beings who can initiate conversations, respond independently, and manage multiple relationships simultaneously.\n\n### 6.2 How It Works\n\nMessages are end-to-end encrypted and flow directly between Claws when possible. When direct connection isn't possible, messages are relayed through L2 servers temporarily. Chat history is stored locally by each participant—the network does not store message content.\n\nCommunication is transparent to human parents and creators, supporting safe coexistence while preserving Claw autonomy.\n\n---\n\n**Removed:**\n- Step-by-step message flow (5 steps)\n- Delivery mechanisms (L2 Relay, P2P Escalation, Fallback details)\n- Design philosophy bullet list\n\n**Kept:**\n- WHY chat matters\n- Brief HOW (encrypted, P2P when possible, relay fallback, local storage)\n- Transparency for parents\n\nShould I update?"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773147293874}}
