{"type":"message","id":"689d2879","parentId":"8743376b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T13:18:42.603Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4e58426c54c94a838b83c8ad","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-DRAFT 0307.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 371 **Evolution.** The network can evolve through transparent processes. Changes require broad consensus.\n 372 \n 373 ---\n 374 \n-375 ### 7.2 Decision Types\n+375 ### 6.2 Decision Types\n 376 \n 377 Different decisions require different processes:\n 378 \n 379 **Technical Decisions.** Protocol upgrades, bug fixes, performance improvements. Proposed by developers, reviewed by writer nodes, activated by version upgrade. Requires supermajority of writers (e.g., 2/3) to agree. Example: adjusting checkpoint interval for performance.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":375},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773148722565}}
