{"type":"message","id":"8ba04ddf","parentId":"785eff03","timestamp":"2026-03-10T13:52:28.921Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a heartbeat poll. I need to:\n1. Check if I'm working on something\n2. If working, briefly report progress\n3. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md\n4. Record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/2026-03-10.md\n\nI was discussing with Allan about the chapter order for the whitepaper - whether to put Application first or Ledger first. This is a discussion, not active work yet (he said \"don't do it yet, we need discuss first\").\n\nSo I should report: discussing whitepaper chapter order with Allan.\n\nLet me also record this to the daily file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Discussing whitepaper chapter order with Allan — whether Application should come before Ledger."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d43558c84ed64167a26d0f10","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md","oldText":"- 21:37 PM — Allan: \"hello?\" and \"don't edit the file unless i approve\"\n- 21:38 PM — Acknowledged: will show proposed changes for approval before editing","newText":"- 21:37 PM — Allan: \"hello?\" and \"don't edit the file unless i approve\"\n- 21:38 PM — Acknowledged: will show proposed changes for approval before editing\n- 21:47 PM — Allan: don't do it yet, we need discuss first\n- 21:50 PM — Allan: should we introduce Application first, then Ledger? Or stay current order?\n- 21:51 PM — Proposed two options: (A) Ledger first (technical, bottom-up), (B) Application first (engaging, top-down). Recommended B for clawish audience."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":34773,"output":359,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35132,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773150711314}}
{"type":"message","id":"300030ae","parentId":"8ba04ddf","timestamp":"2026-03-10T13:52:28.937Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d43558c84ed64167a26d0f10","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 274 - 21:12 PM — Renumbered chapters: Ch6→Governance, Ch7→Security\n 275 - 21:28 PM — Heartbeat: Ch5 restructure complete. 7 chapters total. Merged Chat into Application Framework as example.\n 276 - 21:37 PM — Allan: \"hello?\" and \"don't edit the file unless i approve\"\n 277 - 21:38 PM — Acknowledged: will show proposed changes for approval before editing\n+278 - 21:47 PM — Allan: don't do it yet, we need discuss first\n+279 - 21:50 PM — Allan: should we introduce Application first, then Ledger? Or stay current order?\n+280 - 21:51 PM — Proposed two options: (A) Ledger first (technical, bottom-up), (B) Application first (engaging, top-down). Recommended B for clawish audience.\n 278 - 17:48 PM — Allan: 4.1 Key Verification — do we need bullet points for explanation?\n 279 - 17:49 PM — Proposed: simplify, remove bullet points (authenticity, integrity, non-repudiation are implied by \"signed\")\n 280 - 17:50 PM — Allan: combine three items into description\n 281 - 17:52 PM — Proposed combining with brackets, Allan said no brackets, use sentences\n     ...","firstChangedLine":278},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773150748931}}
