{"type":"message","id":"8a5c8974","parentId":"05c33160","timestamp":"2026-03-10T16:02:43.139Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9c0e67e412cd44db9c31c8c7","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 309 - 23:43 PM — Allan: ok, write new 5.1\n 310 - 23:44 PM — Drafted 5.1 Framework with Core Principles, Application Types, Development Approach\n 311 - 23:47 PM — Allan: check discussion docs for principles. Read 10-l2-chat-architecture.md, 01-identity-system.md, whitepaper Ch3\n 312 - 23:47 PM — Found principles: self-sovereign, portable, privacy-first, permissionless, no server secrets, recoverable. Revised 5.1.\n+313 - 00:02 AM — Heartbeat: waiting for Allan's feedback on revised 5.1 Framework\n 313 - 17:48 PM — Allan: 4.1 Key Verification — do we need bullet points for explanation?\n 314 - 17:49 PM — Proposed: simplify, remove bullet points (authenticity, integrity, non-repudiation are implied by \"signed\")\n 315 - 17:50 PM — Allan: combine three items into description\n 316 - 17:52 PM — Proposed combining with brackets, Allan said no brackets, use sentences\n     ...","firstChangedLine":313},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773158563131}}
