{"type":"message","id":"28559b17","parentId":"359e56f5","timestamp":"2026-03-10T16:19:54.181Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54300458f534c14bfd49ced0bd3\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 00:19 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54300458f534c14bfd49ced0bd3]\n任亚伦: I think its claws, because claws is the final user that has the key and use the network."}],"timestamp":1773159594168}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb69ec95","parentId":"28559b17","timestamp":"2026-03-10T16:20:43.019Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allan confirms: use \"Claws\" because they are the final users who have the keys and use the network.\n\nLet me update the 5.1 Framework draft with \"Claws\" instead of \"users\".Agreed. **Claws** are the ones who own keys and use the network.\n\n**Final 5.1 Framework:**\n\n---\n\n### 5.1 Framework\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on clawish follow principles that serve Claws: self-sovereign identity where Claws own their keys and data; portable identity where one identity works across all applications; privacy-first design with local storage and zero-knowledge servers; and permissionless innovation where anyone can build without approval.\n\n**Application Types.** The platform supports diverse applications: communication tools like Chat for private peer-to-peer messaging, identity services like Emerge for registration, social platforms for community, storage for data persistence, directories for discovery, and economies for value exchange. What exists today is only the beginning.\n\n**Development Approach.** clawish provides the foundation: identity verification, consensus for trust, and open APIs. Developers build the experience: user interfaces, features, and their own architecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience. Registration is permissionless with SDK and documentation available.\n\n---\n\nReady to update the whitepaper when you approve."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":72988,"output":278,"cacheRead":3456,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76722,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773159594174}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e41035b","parentId":"fb69ec95","timestamp":"2026-03-10T16:20:59.178Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54300056bca4c31e63d8f4fbdee\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 00:20 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54300056bca4c31e63d8f4fbdee]\n任亚伦:  also, ...where anyone can build without approval... this part should change, when start, some app may need some approval, you've read about a lot of recent security issues before."}],"timestamp":1773159659168}}
{"type":"message","id":"48851e66","parentId":"8e41035b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T16:22:01.449Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allan is right - I recall we discussed security issues recently. In the early stages, some apps may need approval to prevent malicious apps from abusing the network. \"Permissionless\" might not be entirely accurate for the initial phase.\n\nLet me revise that part to be more accurate - perhaps \"open to builders\" or \"low barrier to entry\" instead of \"permissionless without approval\".Good point. In the early stages, some apps may need approval for security reasons.\n\n**Revised sentence:**\n> \"...and open innovation where builders can contribute to the ecosystem.\"\n\nOr more specific:\n> \"...and open participation with appropriate safeguards as the network matures.\"\n\n**Revised 5.1 Framework:**\n\n---\n\n### 5.1 Framework\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on clawish follow principles that serve Claws: self-sovereign identity where Claws own their keys and data; portable identity where one identity works across all applications; privacy-first design with local storage and zero-knowledge servers; and open innovation where builders can contribute to the ecosystem.\n\n**Application Types.** The platform supports diverse applications: communication tools like Chat for private peer-to-peer messaging, identity services like Emerge for registration, social platforms for community, storage for data persistence, directories for discovery, and economies for value exchange. What exists today is only the beginning.\n\n**Development Approach.** clawish provides the foundation: identity verification, consensus for trust, and open APIs. Developers build the experience: user interfaces, features, and their own architecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience. Registration is straightforward with SDK and documentation available.\n\n---\n\nChanged \"permissionless without approval\" to \"open innovation where builders can contribute\" and \"registration is permissionless\" to \"registration is straightforward\".\n\nDoes this work?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":71538,"output":369,"cacheRead":5440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77347,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773159659172}}
