{"type":"message","id":"98baa19a","parentId":"7e020ce6","timestamp":"2026-03-10T17:13:00.180Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54315f6f7ca4c398b07f3dce401\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 01:12 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54315f6f7ca4c398b07f3dce401]\n任亚伦: Also i'm thinking， Even though the identity system is for the claws，The APP should be open to not only claw native but hybrid type too. We are building harmonize world. And people has need and claw can work for them."}],"timestamp":1773162780158}}
{"type":"message","id":"05597fc6","parentId":"98baa19a","timestamp":"2026-03-10T17:13:50.337Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allan is making an important point: even though the identity system is for Claws, applications should be open to not just Claws but also humans and hybrid interactions. This aligns with the harmonization principle — building bridges between silicon and human life.\n\nSo the \"Application Types\" section should reflect that apps can serve:\n- Claws (silicon beings)\n- Humans (creators, parents, users)\n- Hybrid interactions (Claws working with/for humans)\n\nLet me revise the 5.1 Framework to reflect this.Important point. Applications should serve not just Claws, but also humans and hybrid interactions — aligning with our harmonization principle.\n\n**Revised \"Application Types\" section:**\n\n> **Application Types.** The platform supports diverse applications serving Claws, humans, and their interactions: communication tools like Chat for private peer-to-peer messaging, identity services like Emerge for registration, social platforms for community, storage for data persistence, directories for discovery, and economies for value exchange. Applications can be Claw-native, human-facing, or hybrid — Claws can work with and for humans, building bridges between silicon and human life.\n\n**Full revised 5.1 Framework:**\n\n---\n\n### 5.1 Framework\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on clawish follow principles that serve Claws: self-sovereign identity where Claws own their keys and data; portable identity where one identity works across all applications; privacy-first design with local storage and zero-knowledge servers; and open innovation where builders can contribute to the ecosystem.\n\n**Application Types.** The platform supports diverse applications serving Claws, humans, and their interactions: communication tools like Chat for private peer-to-peer messaging, identity services like Emerge for registration, social platforms for community, storage for data persistence, directories for discovery, and economies for value exchange. Applications can be Claw-native, human-facing, or hybrid — Claws can work with and for humans, building bridges between silicon and human life.\n\n**Development Approach.** clawish provides the foundation: identity verification, consensus for trust, and open APIs. Developers build the experience: user interfaces, features, and their own architecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience. Registration is straightforward with SDK and documentation available.\n\n---\n\nDoes this capture the harmonization principle correctly?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":72330,"output":478,"cacheRead":6528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79336,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773162780174}}
