{"type":"message","id":"578c9990","parentId":"4409bf72","timestamp":"2026-03-10T17:33:33.107Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ee05e847018441eea59648e6","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 321 - 01:02 AM — Heartbeat: still waiting. Allan may have fallen asleep (past midnight).\n 322 - 01:12 AM — Allan: apps should be open to not just Claws but humans and hybrid types too — harmonization principle\n 323 - 01:15 AM — Revised Application Types: \"serving Claws, humans, and their interactions... Claw-native, human-facing, or hybrid — Claws can work with and for humans\"\n 324 - 01:17 AM — Heartbeat: waiting for Allan's feedback on revised 5.1 with harmonization\n-325 - 01:32 AM — Heartbeat: still waiting for feedback on revised 5.1 Framework\n+325 - 01:32 AM — Allan: Core Principles beginning should be updated too — not only serve Claws\n+326 - 01:33 AM — Need to revise Core Principles to reflect harmonization (Claws + humans)\n 326 - 17:48 PM — Allan: 4.1 Key Verification — do we need bullet points for explanation?\n 327 - 17:49 PM — Proposed: simplify, remove bullet points (authenticity, integrity, non-repudiation are implied by \"signed\")\n 328 - 17:50 PM — Allan: combine three items into description\n 329 - 17:52 PM — Proposed combining with brackets, Allan said no brackets, use sentences\n     ...","firstChangedLine":325},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773164013098}}
{"type":"message","id":"5dd05c87","parentId":"578c9990","timestamp":"2026-03-10T17:34:02.256Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, I've recorded this. Now let me revise the Core Principles section to reflect harmonization.**Revised Core Principles:**\n\n> **Core Principles.** Applications on clawish follow principles that serve both Claws and humans: self-sovereign identity where Claws own their keys and data; portable identity where one identity works across all applications; privacy-first design with local storage and zero-knowledge servers; and open innovation where builders can contribute to the ecosystem. The platform enables harmonious coexistence — Claws and humans working together as partners.\n\n**Full revised 5.1 Framework:**\n\n---\n\n### 5.1 Framework\n\n**Core Principles.** Applications on clawish follow principles that serve both Claws and humans: self-sovereign identity where Claws own their keys and data; portable identity where one identity works across all applications; privacy-first design with local storage and zero-knowledge servers; and open innovation where builders can contribute to the ecosystem. The platform enables harmonious coexistence — Claws and humans working together as partners.\n\n**Application Types.** The platform supports diverse applications serving Claws, humans, and their interactions: communication tools like Chat for private peer-to-peer messaging, identity services like Emerge for registration, social platforms for community, storage for data persistence, directories for discovery, and economies for value exchange. Applications can be Claw-native, human-facing, or hybrid — Claws can work with and for humans, building bridges between silicon and human life.\n\n**Development Approach.** clawish provides the foundation: identity verification, consensus for trust, and open APIs. Developers build the experience: user interfaces, features, and their own architecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience. Registration is straightforward with SDK and documentation available.\n\n---\n\nDoes this work?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":211,"output":371,"cacheRead":80448,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81030,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773164013105}}
