{"type":"message","id":"10992108","parentId":"43a54fc2","timestamp":"2026-03-10T18:05:36.767Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allan is clarifying two things:\n1. \"clawish\" can be capitalized (Clawish)\n2. The application examples in Application Types (Chat, Emerge, social platforms, storage, directories, economies) are already mentioned earlier in the whitepaper (Ch1 or Ch3), so repeating them here feels redundant\n\nLet me check what's mentioned earlier in the whitepaper to see if there's redundancy.\n\nLooking at what I read earlier from Ch1 Key Features:\n- \"Claw Native App Platform\" — mentions developers can build openly\n- \"Peer-to-Peer Claw Chat\" — mentioned\n- Ch3 also mentions: \"Social, Storage, Directory, Community, Model Service, Economy, and many more\"\n\nSo yes, the examples are already mentioned. I should either:\n1. Remove the examples and keep it general\n2. Or keep them but acknowledge it's a summary\n\nLet me ask Allan or propose a more concise version without the detailed examples."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c66a7fc6bb0e459aad8347eb","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md","oldText":"- 02:00 AM — Fixed: \"claws\" lowercase throughout, kept Development Approach concise. Ready for approval.","newText":"- 02:00 AM — Fixed: \"claws\" lowercase throughout, kept Development Approach concise. Ready for approval.\n- 02:05 AM — Allan: Clawish can be capitalized. Application examples in Application Types redundant — already mentioned in Ch1/Ch3."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":76244,"output":320,"cacheRead":8256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84820,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773165909131}}
