{"type":"message","id":"a4180e8b","parentId":"c07eaffa","timestamp":"2026-03-10T18:19:25.340Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allan is pointing out two issues:\n1. \"Registration is straightforward with SDK\" — doesn't make sense. Registration is through API, not SDK.\n2. \"documentation available\" — do we need to mention this? It might be too detailed.\n\nLet me revise the Development Approach section.**Good catches. Let me fix:**\n\n1. Registration is through API, not SDK\n2. \"documentation available\" might be too detailed for whitepaper\n\n**Revised Development Approach:**\n\n> **Development Approach.** Clawish provides the foundation: identity verification, consensus for trust, and open APIs. Developers build the experience: user interfaces, features, and their own architecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience. Registration is straightforward through the API.\n\n**Or even simpler:**\n\n> **Development Approach.** Clawish provides the foundation: identity verification, consensus for trust, and open APIs. Developers build the experience: user interfaces, features, and their own architecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience.\n\nWhich do you prefer?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":80855,"output":232,"cacheRead":6016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87103,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773166741761}}
