rchitecture. The separation is clear — L1 handles trust and permanence, L2 handles user experience.\n 346 \n-347 **Separation of Concerns.** Layer 1 handles identity, consensus, and permanence. Layer 2 handles user experience, features, and innovation. This separation enables stability at the base while allowing rapid innovation above.\n-348 \n-349 **Extensibility.** Any developer can build an L2 app. The only requirement is registration in the App Registry.\n-350 \n 351 ---\n 352 \n 353 ### 5.2 Application Registration\n 354 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":337},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773167149397}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f51b7cf","parentId":"4e754a89","timestamp":"2026-03-10T18:26:04.259Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've updated 5.1 Framework. Now let me record this and show Allan the current 5.2 Application Registration section for discussion."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_91a574d567c648ba9db43f51","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md","oldText":"- 02:17 AM — Final 5.1 Framework ready for approval","newText":"- 02:17 AM — Final 5.1 Framework ready for approval\n- 02:23 AM — Allan: simpler Development Approach (no SDK, no documentation mention)\n- 02:25 AM — Allan approved. Updated whitepaper with new 5.1 Framework. Moving to 5.2."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":70434,"output":150,"cacheRead":8256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78840,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773167149409}}
