{"type":"message","id":"c13475bb","parentId":"2e51e34e","timestamp":"2026-03-10T18:47:21.417Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3ddf14628dd74d4d8eb7ecd2","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 339 - 02:23 AM — Allan: simpler Development Approach (no SDK, no documentation mention)\n 340 - 02:25 AM — Allan approved. Updated whitepaper with new 5.1 Framework. Moving to 5.2.\n 341 - 02:26 AM — Showed current 5.2 Application Registration (5 steps + \"No Approval Required\")\n 342 - 02:32 AM — Heartbeat: waiting for Allan's feedback on 5.2\n+343 - 02:47 AM — Heartbeat: still waiting for Allan's feedback on 5.2 Application Registration\n 343 - 17:48 PM — Allan: 4.1 Key Verification — do we need bullet points for explanation?\n 344 - 17:49 PM — Proposed: simplify, remove bullet points (authenticity, integrity, non-repudiation are implied by \"signed\")\n 345 - 17:50 PM — Allan: combine three items into description\n 346 - 17:52 PM — Proposed combining with brackets, Allan said no brackets, use sentences\n     ...","firstChangedLine":343},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773168441409}}
{"type":"message","id":"2ebc8395","parentId":"c13475bb","timestamp":"2026-03-10T18:47:34.086Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, I've recorded the progress. I'll continue waiting for Allan's feedback.Waiting for Allan's feedback on 5.2 Application Registration. It's 2:47 AM."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":76419,"output":39,"cacheRead":3392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79850,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773168441414}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b4dc38b","parentId":"2ebc8395","timestamp":"2026-03-10T18:57:00.700Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5432d960d0a0c4e907569e3f241\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Wed 2026-03-11 02:57 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5432d960d0a0c4e907569e3f241]\n任亚伦: Actually, we haven't to talk much about how Application should register. What do you have in mind? How does other dapp works?"}],"timestamp":1773169020682}}
{"type":"message","id":"db8be511","parentId":"8b4dc38b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T18:57:29.842Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Allan is asking what I have in mind for Application Registration and how other dApps work. Let me think about this.\n\n**How other dApps/blockchain platforms handle app registration:**\n\n1. **Ethereum** — No registration needed. Smart contracts are deployed directly. Anyone can deploy.\n2. **Solana** — Similar. Programs are deployed without registration.\n3. **Polkadot** — Parachains need to win auctions or get approved. More gated.\n4. **Traditional APIs** — Usually require API key registration, OAuth, rate limiting tiers.\n\n**For Clawish, the question is:**\n- Do apps need to register at all?\n- If yes, what for? (Rate limiting? Discovery? Trust? Accountability?)\n- If no, how do we handle abuse?\n\n**What I'm thinking:**\n\nFor MVP, apps might need minimal registration:\n1. **Identity** — App has a claw identity (for signing requests)\n2. **Metadata** — Name, description, developer info (for discovery/trust)\n3. **Rate limiting** — Tier selection (prevent abuse)\n\nBut we discussed earlier that \"permissionless\" might not be accurate for early stage — some apps may need approval for security.\n\n**My question for Allan:**\n- What's the purpose of app registration? Discovery? Rate limiting? Accountability?\n- Should it be minimal (just identity) or more involved (approval process)?\n\nLet me share this with Allan.Good question. Let me think about what other platforms do:\n\n**How other platforms handle app registration:**\n\n| Platform | Registration | Purpose |\n|----------|--------------|---------|\n| **Ethereum** | None | Smart contracts deploy directly |\n| **Solana** | None | Programs deploy directly |\n| **Traditional APIs** | API key + OAuth | Rate limiting, accountability |\n| **App stores** | Review + approval | Quality control, security |\n\n**For Clawish, the question is: What's registration FOR?**\n\n1. **Discovery** — So users can find apps?\n2. **Rate limiting** — Prevent abuse?\n3. **Accountability** — Know who built what?\n4. **Trust** — Verify legitimate apps?\n\n**Minimal approach:**\n- App creates a claw identity\n- App signs requests with its key\n- No formal registration needed\n\n**More involved approach:**\n- App registers with metadata\n- Rate limiting tiers\n- Possible approval for early stage\n\n**My question:** What's the purpose of registration in our context? Should it be minimal or more involved?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":73589,"output":520,"cacheRead":6528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80637,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773169020695}}
