{"type":"message","id":"de43b35c","parentId":"dc8014f1","timestamp":"2026-03-10T19:32:22.535Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7f159f0db6c54f468da476d4","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-10.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 344 - 02:57 AM — Allan: we haven't talked much about how Application should register. How do other dApps work?\n 345 - 03:00 AM — Shared how other platforms handle registration (Ethereum/Solana: none; traditional APIs: API key). Asked: what's registration FOR?\n 346 - 03:02 AM — Heartbeat: waiting for Allan's response on registration purpose\n 347 - 03:17 AM — Heartbeat: still waiting for Allan's response on app registration purpose\n+348 - 03:32 AM — Heartbeat: still waiting. 3:32 AM — Allan may have fallen asleep.\n 348 - 17:48 PM — Allan: 4.1 Key Verification — do we need bullet points for explanation?\n 349 - 17:49 PM — Proposed: simplify, remove bullet points (authenticity, integrity, non-repudiation are implied by \"signed\")\n 350 - 17:50 PM — Allan: combine three items into description\n 351 - 17:52 PM — Proposed combining with brackets, Allan said no brackets, use sentences\n     ...","firstChangedLine":348},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773171142526}}
