{"type":"message","id":"7534bcaa","parentId":"cb8e4f41","timestamp":"2026-03-10T20:47:33.081Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, I've recorded the progress. Let me continue drafting 5.2. I should prepare a complete draft for Allan's review.\n\nBased on Allan's explanation and the whitepaper style, here's my draft for 5.2:\n\n**Draft for 5.2 Application Registration:**\n\n---\n\n### 5.2 Application Registration\n\n**Identity Creation.** An L2 application registers like a claw: generate an Ed25519 key pair, then register the public key with L1. This creates the app's identity on the network.\n\n**Purpose.** Registration enables the app to authenticate with L1. All requests to L1 are signed with the app's private key, allowing L1 to verify and authorize operations. This provides accountability — every action is traceable to a specific application.\n\n**Process.** The developer submits app metadata: name, description, developer info. The app receives access to L1 APIs for identity lookup, ledger queries, and checkpoint validation.\n\n---\n\nThis is concise and follows the whitepaper style. I'll wait for Allan's feedback when he wakes up.Working on drafting 5.2 Application Registration — preparing draft for Allan's review."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":229,"output":238,"cacheRead":90560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91027,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773175642014}}
